\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 1897.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 The place where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 The town - 200 Mott Lane, it was a public house in Thwaites, Keighley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 That's a district of Keighley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Thwaites. Keighley. Thwaites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But it's actually in Keighley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, it's - that would be in Keighley, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Can you remember how long you lived in that house where you were born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What you call what - I was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How long you lived in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. 
Lived in twice, we came out of the public house and then went back again. Now my mother died when I was - in 1905 when I was - eight years of age you see, and we - we came out right away, therefore I had lived - well I'd lived eight years and - yes, eight
 years, that's correct, yes, eight years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You came out of the Shoulder of Mutton because your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Died, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you go into a house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, we went into a - we - we went in with this - one of my sisters, one of my sist
ers you see, my father's daughter and - weith - her four children, you see, there'd four left, the four was off you see, and the four - was at home, and he - he went - we all went with him you see to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Your father and the four of you who were left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. With -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You went with a sister who was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Married, that's correct, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not - not so very long. We weren't long there because she came out of that house into - a beer off shop in the same lit
tle village, and we weren't there above - both houses we weren't there above two years, before my father got married again and I was ten year old you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was that when you went back to the Shoulder of Mutton then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, when he married again, no,
 it - we moved - only about a - a mile away in the same area you see. In Keighley you see, from - where we were in the village of Thwaites. We were in the village of Thwaites and then we moved - just about a mile away in Dalton Lane you see, wasn't - and 
w
e lived there you see, well - one of them - one of the boys, one of the four wouldn't come home, he went into lodgings you see, but the four - three of us lived with me step-mother you see. I was married from my stepmother, she was a wonderful woman, she 
-
 you know, she was quite nice. Of course I was the youngest lad and she made a fair bit of me and - want - wanted me to go into an office when I was in the mill. Not that she was thinking about - she wouldn't have overalls to wash, she wouldn't have to ge
t up six o'clock you see, because - office work was half past eight you see, those were the early morning hours.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You say you went back to the Shoulder of Mutton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was that after you were married then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, it - wait a minute
, I'm going too fast. About 1905 my father came out you see. No, I'm overriding myself there. We came out of the Shoulder of Mutton when I was about three. We went onto a farm. And then - we left the farm to go to a - another public house in town. Went ba
ck to another area. Moved back into that area, this is - that's all in a - a short time and then went back into the public house and then it was - my mother died when I was eight. I'm sorry about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Which of these places would you live in the longest then as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh - the - there at the - the public house do you see. Yes, because I lived there for a year and go back perhaps for two, so I'd lived five of it - ten years, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 There were eight of you altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Brothers and sisters, what order did they come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 There was - girl - boy, girl. Three - four - four boys and then a girl the last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 About how much time was there between each?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well if you got eight - you - I think there'll be a right big ga
p between - I think that the highest gap was four and - four and a half years see, all the others would be two I should think you know. Should work it out really you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Where did you come in, were you the last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 The last - the last boy, yes, that's correct.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes - forty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Locally. Oakley I think up - yes, Oakworth, yes, think -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 He was a textile - textile fitter. But he went all over the world practically you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Setting machines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Machinery, textile, that's the woollens you know, the Flatt Brothers, printers and textiles, the big - they're in the big combine perhaps you know. Mm. Now. He went in Russia 
and America and - France, Germany, all these place - but he wouldn't he'd been to America - he'd never been to Australia, said it was too far. But you see that time in fact my mother was running the pub with the - help of the family you see, they were gro
wing up you see, they could do it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your father have any other job before or after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, he stuck even - after he came out of the public house he - he went into the - and worked for a local firm, but wouldn't go far, he did round t
he West Riding you see, going out - and repairing the machines for them, resetting them up you know, leveling them and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 
When he came out of the public house he - he went back a bit after he retired but not for long you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did he ever do any casual or part time work of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
I don't think so, no. He was in business for himself, and - that was when he was at the Shoulder of Mutton, even when he was that, and - when he came out he - he just have done very well because - he bought a - 
a block - a block of four back to back houses that were just built, first one that was built just at the back of the public house for seven hundred pound cash and then he bought two right up the brow of the hill at the back of it, the Thwaites brow, and -
 so - he must have done pretty well I should think you see, he wouldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 mortgage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  them, he'd buy them straight down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You mean he was working on setting machines on his own account?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, well - yes, well his partner, was two fellows, two other fellows, and they were - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 textile}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 repairers and removers you see, the - removing the machines from one mill to another and leveling them off you see. And there'd be spare parts as well, they'd be making the spare parts for the machines that - a few firms in - l
ike that, there'd one across the road, a chap across the road has done very well in it lately, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. I didn't worry much like because he'd this income of six houses you see and he also had a bit o
f money. He was for a period but - oh I'll tell you a funny story. When I was at school you see, now the time came when you got to be twelve - and thirteen, sitting for a - an examination to go to the grammar school you see. Well I was pretty - smart, a g
ood - very good }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 mathematician}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 you see, I wasn't brilliant at - most - a lot of things, but that was a gift because I could - I never met anybody as quick on mental arithmetic you see, and the boss at work used to say oh my - he said something about earning 
your living on the music hall at this job, and he'd be - taking a pen - a pencil out to write it what it was. I told him you see and - he'd look up you see. It was a gift mind you, some people have, just a certain gift, and that was mine and that's why - 
I got on pretty well. But how far was I getting to now. Carried away with my own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 enthusiasm}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 I've lost my - oh after work, that was it wasn't it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 Well - he said - they were asking me were the teachers, this lady, well they were both lady and a gentleman, why
 couldn't I go in for this you know, because the - they wanted somebody with this skill to pass and I was - well I was head of the class, I was pretty fair at - English you know and just the ordinary things. I wouldn't make a good scientist or a - anyhow 
- oh I said - and just at that time me father was - out of work you see, oh I said, I'm sorry, I said, me father's out of work, you know, and - you know, and he'd go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 t the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570  income from six houses you see like, it was nearly a wage in those days, you know, wouldn't be a wage, and - I got away with it that way you see and I had to tell them I would be in a job before long. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Saved me bacon a bit like that. I was sorry afterwards. When it got - in later in life you see I could have had more education, quicker you s
ee, I was self-taught you see, I'd have been better - you see, had I been - so more confidence in yourself when you - when you had that education, there's no doubt about that is there. But, mind you, the three other boys that did go, and I didn't you see,
 
they weren't - didn't get in good as positions as I had eventually you see. One is in the Town Hall in the Treasury and - one was in a clothing shop you see, but - I did better than them with just specializing you see on - on accountancy you see, it stood
 me in good stead with the figuring you see, and memory.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Same age as - same age - I think they were both the same age. Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Tadcaster. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Had she any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
I don't think so, she'd - probably be a - a servant you see, you know, used to do work in the houses. I've an idea she was, I couldn't tell you that moment - one sister - I was - I won't - I've no sisters living, th
at's all out of eight. One the youngest one, she's working yet. And - I've one at eighty - going eighty-seven but she's in hospital now. She's - half - threequarters of the time she'll talk just as she did on - then she'll wander on and tell you all such 
a
 fancy story you know. Her minds going you see, but she's very frail you see. Nearly eighty-seven. So you might have a chance yet to get to know that - just little thing about - what my mother did before - but I think - that she'd come from a farm in Eire
 you see - where - she'd either work on the farm if she had one and - you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. I don't think - my mother would. I've never heard that mentioned at all. No, didn't - and - I think - it would have been ment
ioned, see well I was eight. Oh no she wouldn't only in the - in the public house you see because - all the time - she were bringing up family you see. No, she wouldn't work - until she got into the public house you see. Which would be - she died in 1905,
 
and I - I should think we've have been there ten years before that you see. She was fifty. That was forty, she - she should work from forty see in the public house so naturally they'd all do - she'd have enough on her plate with all the family without doi
ng a lot of work, because the eldest sisters would do a lot of the work in the public house you see. That's to being eight, but I don't - I know - bits but I don't know all the full story. As a child you don't - don't gather it all in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But she would run the public house while you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
While me father - while me father was away working you see. He - he was in charge you see but when he was off - these jobs took him away a long time you see, but - naturally when he - he - when he was a bit h
ome, on the textile machinery parts - it would be home you see and - and he'd be when the work - he'd do it at the night you see. But do you know in those days you see there's - the Corporation Gasworks was about - oh half a mile away, and they used to co
m
e off the shifts half past five and we opened at six o'clock in the morning, they'd come up for the drinks at - six o'clock in the morning. Open full days in those days, right through you know, full days. Half past six to - half past eleven, twelve o'cloc
k at night you see. No }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 license}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  hours, no, no. I remember all that, and eggs and - free nuts and all that you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Your mother would be looking after the children herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, we had one - she wasn't a resident, but we had a - some - they c
all them servants in those days you see, come in - all day - all - during the day you see and perhaps at night. 'Cos we'd have more than one but I know one in particular here, was here, with us a long time, but we've had - we'd have others as well you see
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How many rooms were there eat the Shoulder of Mutton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Was a big living room, and there was a - we'd a sort of a lounge which was used the weekends, for the public. Then we'd a big tap room, a big passage, bar and then a small lounge and a big c
lub room sort of you see. So there's one, two, three - we've got five downstairs - no - yes, with that - we don't count the bar do we? There'd be five rooms downstairs not counting the bar you see. Living lounge, tap room, another small lounge and a club 
room was used at weekend.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How many bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Now then - there's certain to be four, yes. Because that club room was a - single story place you see so there wouldn't be a - a - something above that. It was one of these - dove shapes like you know
, of course and - might, I think you could say four bedrooms. And naturally there wouldn't be a - an indoor toilet or a bathroom inside in those days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 There'd be a kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, there - there - one at the back was a kitchen. Well it was din - dining kitchen you know. All combined you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Is this the living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, that's right, living - yes, a living room kitchen combined you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live there? Did you have any other relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, I don't - I can't remember anyone. We had come to stay for a bit but I can never remember anyone - living any period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 This servant that you had, you say there's one you remember very well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did she live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, she didn't live in, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What were her duties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well she mostly you see there were a lot of stone floor in those days you see and I mean wash - scrubbing them you see, stone floors and the - wooden tables most of them, an
d - one - seats and - in the tap room round the side and - and stone floor, sanded, and - helped the - of course you won't have seen them, spittoons with sawdust in you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 So that she was largely engaged on cleaning then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, that's right, cleaning, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did she look after the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 She'd help, yes, definitely, because - I was one of them you see. She would help.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What sort of house did she work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Now then that's - well I couldn't say you see, that's a difficult thing to ask you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 
Of course she had a family of her own, she'd a few of her own, I know, one of them came to work with us - where I was at - in fact when I was in charge in the company that I - Russelside Company, Keighley, one of her daughters came to work for us and -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would she work sort of part time would you say? Or nearer full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well it'd be part time in a way, in those - in those days, but she put a lot of hours in, she'd come every day you see. Saturday, might be off at Sunday like, and she might come then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 All right, I liked yes, she was a very nice person. Oh yes, quite nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What did she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 She called us all by name, see, Sam and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about your mother, what did she call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well she - I think she called her Mrs Wigglesworth I think, yes, I don't think - I can't remember her getting on intimate terms, me mother was very - ordinary, a lovable person you know, you know, she was a - she wasn't wh
at you could call a publican - I can tell you a story about - they used to rant in those days, people did - they'd go on a rant for seven days or a week, a week or a - fortnight you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 
No they wouldn't - would go home just to eat sometimes, go out in the
 morning and - of course pubs were open you see, and they'd come there you see, well - what could you do, if - if - if you didn't serve 'em they'd go somewhere else and perhaps get into worse company and - now one fellow - I was - I got - late in life I g
o
 pally with him and - got pally with his son and - they lived somewhere about, and I - I went to his mother's house, and you know, she said - I don't know how we'd have got on but for your mother, she said, when - my - so and so's ranting she says used to
 bring us flour and everything, provisions, she said. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Mm. She would get a little bit but she was giving it back you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 This lady who worked for her, what did you call her, did you call her Mrs whatever it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. Well I think I - I - I cal
led her Sarah Elizabeth, and my - naturally it got to be Sarlizzie. Sarlizzie you see. It was always Sarlizzie you know, Sarah Lizzie, you know. It even got Sarah when it's put together it was Sarlizzie. Well - I expect - you get that from children callin
g it you see, you couldn't say Sarah Lizzie perhaps you'd say Sar Elizabeth, you'd say Sarlizzie.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes, I can never remember - but she'd help with it you see, would - yes, they called her Holt, Mrs Holt, Sarah E
lizabeth Holt, yes. She had a time on because he'd been an ex-soldier, he wouldn't work when he came back so - that's why I expect she had to - bring a family and he'd - you know a bit of a scrounger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your mother or father make or mend any of the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh yes, me mother would - yes, as was usual, they'd all do the shirt repairing you know and trousers and - you know, the - all the - all the plain repairs you see, they'd do that, yes, oh yes. In - in fact maybe little - my wife use
d to do a part for me you see in our day, but when things come you see you don't bother, you throw 'em out or - darn socks occasionally but they don't bother to darn socks most of them now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 In those days, things would be tighter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, uh huh. Oh
 yes, that's right, we hadn't the money for it then. 'Cos the average words - wage I'm talking about that would be about - twenty-eight shillings a week for an engineer you see well - the labourers got only sixteen shillings you see that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would most of your clothes be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh yes, they'd be bought you see. Oh well - the younger girls might make a penny or such as that, my mother you see but - same as she wouldn't make a - make a suit you see for me you see and shirt, she'd buy those. An
d then mend them when - it was necessary to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Where would you go to buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
In the local - shops. Yes, just in the - in the local - ready made tailor shops you see, and - and the - girls, the - the milliners, dressmakers you see. 'Cos they -
 they - they did very fair did - our family, you see, with - just being a wee bit better off than the area you see, 'cos it was a poor area where we lived, with my father you see just getting on a bit better we'd just be a bit wee better off and the girls
 would be - better dressed than - the - those running round - the village you see, so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 About how often would you all have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well - that varies you see because - you see when you're growing up you see that - wear each others, as they d
o in a big family. Well you see with a young person - growing meant - you can't - he must have a pretty regular because you'd grow out of them in those days you see so - you'd have to have them - you'd either have them - pretty often or wear your others y
ou see and then - perhaps you'd get playing in - in the others, you - you say, I want a new suit you see and you get one, you know, but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Some people would have them for a special occasion, like the Sunday school anniversary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, well that's al
l - we were always dolled up for Whit Monday, to go to the church, the - sort of party and we went to the local - St Mary's church and - and - we was always dressed up you know and take your own pot with you and get a bun and carry on singing and - games 
and sports in the evening. But everybody'd be dressed up for that - period you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But you'd have new clothes at other times as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Oh yes, just then, but - the mother's'd generally see that - they got the children as nice as they possib
ly could, you know, even - in those days, they were proud of them you know, they wanted them to be - as nice as anybody else. Oh there'd be exception to the rule but you'd find it that - that was the case. Most case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about shoes in your family? Would they be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Now - most of us you see we wore clogs - at school you see we all wore clogs at school. And - there was - brass buttons, brass - toes or - iron, sheet iron toes the - the - we all had brass ones because mother said they're more d
ressy, she didn't like them - the - sheet iron toes, they were - more square, they looked too rough she said, so we'd all to wear - brass, these little brass studs you see on them, they did look - smarter, they just had more shine on them. Yes. And - got 
our shoes - we were all right you see but - some kids in - the village were - right poorly like, wear right through and wear 'em 'til they - you know, they're coming through and - we were fortunate. We get them pretty often you see without any trouble.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about repairing them, would you go to a cloggers or would your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, me father didn't do any - ironing. No, and I don't think he was that much of a shoemaker, no. We'd go to the local - shoemaker you see and - there was a clogger there at
 - that cut his own wood soles for the clogs as well, he cut the soles. And made the clogs, he was a clogmaker you see in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I know your father was away a good deal but did he help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, he was a good worker, and - if it's necessary he would - you know a bit in the home as well, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What sort of things would he do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well on the catering side he would help you see, you know he was - pretty handy that way, he was a cook, he 
could cook, not a cook by trade but he could - he was a good cook, I remember having a - I've never been able to cook at all, never bothered, but me father I - Sundays, he'd always cook the Sunday meal when we got - later in life you see, always cooked th
e Sunday meal. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 He'd cook both for the family and the catering in the public house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well there wouldn't be much catering, they may have made sandwiches occasionally for them, but he'd do that you see. Of course, although - things are bad we'
d always have a big - well plenty to eat, 'cos we'd sandwiches, cheese, always plenty of cheese and a - and a big joint you see in those days. And he'd make cheese sandwiches you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did he do anything like cleaning or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Me father do
 his share of washing up in the - in bar and all that you see but I don't know whether he'd do a lot - in the house you see, me mother was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would he do things like making the fire or doing decorating or repairs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh ye
s, he used to - he'd make the fires up you see in the morning and do that sort of work you know oh yes, do that. And - I don't think - he was - I can't remember him being very much of a decorator you see, like and - no, it seemed more like a one man job I
 think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did he do any repairs or improvements to the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Can't remember him doing anything at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did he do anything for you as children like dressing or undressing or bathing you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh he yes did, not - 
no, not much - only when - he'd help when - when the - I was eight and - my sister was six, when we went to live with - my sister you see, his daughter - he helped then you see, he'd help to - see us to bed and all that you know Of course it wouldn't be u
ndressing like six and eight but - if you're bathing or owt like that he'd help you see if there's anything to do like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But he didn't when your mother was a live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, no, he haven't done much then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did he read to you or tell you stories?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. No, he wasn't a man that was a - a right lot of - patience with children you know, he was - a big hard you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 Well he wasn't - nasty you know, but he was very - the olden days they were so firm with you, you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. You do what - you know, if 
he spoke you stop where you were you see, but today like it - different altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did he take you out at all without your mother? Or look after you while she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, it were more or less always looked after ourselves, there wasn't much -
 taking out you see. No, we'd play around in the village and - go to school, and - have the fun that way you see. Look forward to - Sunday school outings occasionally to - Newsome Dene, that sort of thing. Look Keighley you know and the stream there, big 
old - wagonettes you know and - old carts with sides up you know from the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you have any tasks to carry out in the home as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I can see them more after - me father got married again, when I was - ten. I'd have bits - oh I r
emember doing them when I - I did 'em for a penny not - none of that - young, perhaps I'd want to do it, used to do something, clean out the spittoons, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 sawdust}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  with a stick you see, didn't get your hand on it, cleaning it all out you know, put it round
 the back yard somewhere and - we'd a big yard at the back of the public house, and - put 'em on where I should do and - swilling them out at a tap we had outside and - taking them back, that sort of thing. Such jobs like that you know, you - you'd do you
 
see. It might be - you see, there's always some - nuts or something, they always kept - tons of nuts, they used to give 'em away in the tap room you see, well then - she'd have 'em in a cupboard you see, she'd always give you some if you'd do bits of jobs
 for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But it was sort of voluntary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Voluntary more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 It wasn't a task assigned to you as a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, I can't remember - in those days, but as I say - when I was ten year old, this'll be in your period - 1907, and me
 father got married - again, the three of us went with home but - the one that - the eldest one that - well it was the eldest of the four, he came back eventually you see and thought - he thought he'd like to come back he wouldn't like it in lodgings so -
 
he - he came back home with us, there's four of us, now - we had - the two of us I know - the others were working, the two eldest and - myself and the sister weren't. And we'd all sorts of jobs to do. At - at Saturday morning that was it, we'd - we'd to c
l
ean the knives and forks, there weren't all this stainless steel they're the old kind, we'd those to clean and - I'd always to clean my father's shoes at weekend for him to go work on Monday morning. And - the back yard to swill with water you know and a 
b
rush. And - like bits - things like - oh and me sister had to - I think she had to make her own bed and - clean up the swills you know upstairs and - in those days you see. Bits of jobs, washing up but - oh you all - given bits of jobs like that in the ho
m
e you see. We weren't allowed to come in, sit down a meal and walk out you see, you - those - even when the - even me sister see when she was working she got to be full time she'd be doing fifty - but she didn't go to the evening classes like I did, see m
e doing, but she had bits of jobs to car - allocated to her you see to do you see, oh yes, didn't get away with it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you continue doing these things after you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  school or was it just your sister that did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, I think I - I'd go on
 doing them for a while, yes. Yes, I don't know how long, of course I - I went into the Army at nineteen, the first two years I - excused. Oh yes, I'd do bits of jobs like - I'd help you see - you know. Because she was - they were getting older you see th
ey were in the sixties you see and I'd help a bit just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did the older children help the younger ones with things they found difficult, like dressing or eating or look after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, they'd always - they - when we were at the Shoulder of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 Mutton}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 they'd all pull and - and - especially the two eldest sisters you see. They'd look after the young ones, we two like of course I was a boy but still she - they'd help and - and look after us you know, and see to us you see, like to relive my mo
ther you see, before they got married you see. In fact the eldest sister got married, came back to the same pub but she didn't stay there long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did the younger children help the older ones then with anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, I don't think so. No, they're not to, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time as a schoolchild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Yes, yes, we were very strictly brought up and always had to - you know, occasionally it might just break off it but - usually we knew what time was, make our way in an
d sometimes - a special game we might stick it past get - a clip under the ear when we got back you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 About what time would you have to be in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well this - it varied naturally you see as you got older. Naturally, you'd be in by eight, nin
e you see when you're - you were a young - then, it's be about when I was ten you see I think it'd be about nine o'clock you see. But you see it varied in winter and summer you see, sometimes they let you play out a bit longer in the summer nice weather, 
dark you see they - they're apt to bring you in sooner you see, not letting you keep - stay out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was it your mother who put you to bed or one of your older sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well when we're young kiddies - mother being downstairs and busy - they always -
 older sister would help that you see, that - part you see, well - they'd change about if a couple are old enough you see to - look after the public - they're eighteen you see or twenty you see well they're - women, young women you see and they were helpi
ng in the bar you see, they'd help in the bar and then - help getting us to bed if mother was in the bar she'd - you know, they'd work it amongst them see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How old would you be when you started putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well that's a - well I - I 
know I was - definitely know nowt about it when I was - ten I know that but going back in - well you see after eight you see then - oh - we'd run - I'd run up to bed on me own like, six I should think you know, or seven anyhow, seven, and - yes, anything 
special - they'd come perhaps and do it like but I never had any - of course I know - ten I - nothing in it my stepmother put me to bed you know at ten year old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I - I had - now - there was a - on
e - oh at - oh you mean - I - I keep chopping about from - now the Shoulder of Mutton. Yes, I think we slept together, my sister and I 'til we were about - five I think, you know, the younger sister, she was two years younger than me. And then - I think t
h
ey found her a - a bed on her own or got something - and then there was - brothers, sometimes - we'd sleep two brothers together, but - when I got to be about twelve - it was I - I don't know whether I was growing up and - I didn't want to sleep with anyb
ody else you know, it's funny, yes. No, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 never slept}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  with anybody after that, until I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When you were all at home what were the sleeping arrangements, you say that there were four bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, well that was at the - later on when my
 father got married again I'm coming to. Will that do for you? But, I won't have as much idea about sleeping arrangements - you see when I was - eight and under, you see, at the public house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Where were you then, when your father got married again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Into Dalton Lane. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I think we'd better stick to the Shoulder of Mutton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 If you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Mm. Well there'd be - two - two grown up - young woman you see, and there were youngest - oh it'd be six when my mother di
ed you see. Well they all - they all had one room of their own, because there were four bedrooms you see. Now there was - five - lads first you see, well naturally two bedrooms would be sufficient for five in those days. And then me father and mother in t
he big room you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You hadn't got a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, no, there was no bathroom there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What were the arrangements for bathing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well there were the old - tin bath you know that's all, and - in the kitchen they'd have to do it when it
 was convenient when everybody had gone to bed, you know. Fit it in best way they could you see. Oh I think there was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did you manage with a large number like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Out house, well they could have done it in there you see, they'd have had
 to take the water to it you see. It was - of course it was never - I never - you see, when you're only small you don't realize much like what's going on as - you do in the older ones you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But what about yourself, do you remember what the arrangement was as far as you were concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well up to eight you see we - we could - nobody bother you see and - in the kitchen you see like - you know. Certain - Friday night you see and - we - weekend you see, Friday night }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 bath night
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  type of - my mother 
just set the water in you see and - you had to get into it. Of course if I got to eight she might - you know, sister be six you see she'd say well - you clear off you see like - you see, just keep you apart do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you have clean clothes to put on related to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 bath nights}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, well - yes, we - we - well used to work - work it that way - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 
bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  you see we get our clean clothes and weekly wash you know and clean - clean clothes, underwear and socks, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Where did the family have its meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
In this big - living room down - a long table you see, well it - I think it take we all eight you see I think, yes, that was a right long table you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were there any occasions when you'd eat anywhere else, in any other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No
, I don't think it was necessary. We could have gone - if - there had been a big party, we had a clubroom, it was called that because - the sick club met there of a - Monday evening and called it the club room you see, it was a local sick - but it's just 
b
een disbanded now, forget the name of it, and it - it was always the clubroom and it was a - a sort of a - square room but looking outside it was like - sloped up into a peak like a dome on the top you see, it was a very nice room. And - I've an idea we'v
e
 had - parties in there, if it had been anything special you see but - wedding parties if any of them got married you see was this - lounge you see. Of course they may have given - let that room, I think we did for bits of parties you see, you could have 
a drink you see and - have that room as well you see and - for a party you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 The cooking would be done in this room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 It would be done in that same room too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What was it, was it a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, we had a big range there but I can't
 - just see the type, it was an old - big open fire I know it was a big one you see, it was an old public house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Wasn't there any other sort of equipment, you know, gas or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Can't remember that properly. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When y
ou were going to school what were the arrangements about breakfast? Would you all have breakfast together or would different people have it at different times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well you see, the - the eldest my - in that period - the eldest would - be off to work at 
six o'clock you see. You see, and - we that were going to school you see up to - twelve, well - only go up to eight, see we'd have our breakfast, go to school for half past eight you see. We'd have our breakfast about quarter to eight you see. We might - 
they might have whipped it up a bit sooner than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 So it was the younger children who would have breakfast about quarter to eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well she - she'd have it in between I should say or after 
she had got the - the others off to the mill or some - the - the engineer shops you see. There was two engineers, one - and one a tailor and - another worked in the mill at that time you see because he wouldn't be ready for his trade you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did they manage for their breakfast, did they have a breakfast before they went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh, they had a - a sort of a drink and off to work. Now in the mills the - excuse me, breakfast was - at the mill half - eight o'clock to half past. They'd take a bit of so
mething with them you see. And they - they'd all have cans you see, you know, hold about - a pint and a half of tea, they'd take their tea in it and - the lad in the mill, he'd take it down to the boiler house where the hot water was and fill all the cans
 
up you see. They'd have their cans, the mill'd - they'd keep it at the mill you see and - take their tea and sugar, put it in and - milk in a bottle and - and he'd bring it up at the break, they might have stayed at lunch time they'd do the same you see, 
b
ut - that's how it was worked - in - all have cans, they'd go down and - well I handled the job, I did the job once, you'd take about - a dozen in each hand, cans with handles on you know down to the boiler house you see. Bring them all back. Then at - Ch
ristmas and holiday times - you looked forward to a bit of a tip from all of them you see, like as - as holiday and Christ - Christmas, the boy that did it. All a job - called him a jobber lad you see, did odd jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What did you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well it - we always had plenty of porridge you see 'cos we - were always getting plenty of - stuff to eat, it might have been not too fancy but - and occasionally get an egg and bacon you see but - won't get it every morning you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you have anything special on a Sunday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, I can't say we'd any - oh Sunday - always have something special at Sunday tea, you know, we'd have - although if we had - you - you know, they go on to the old prunes and custard you know, and - and - sweet l
oaf you see, always special tea. But - it's one thing I never liked and that was - these little seeds in the cake, there's two things I don't like, that's one of them. What do you call it? A seed cake, what they call a seed - oh, I'll think of it. Mm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about something to drink at breakfast time, did you have tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Tea, yes, always tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What sort of a meal did you have at dinnertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh we'd just the usual - well we always seemed to have meat, we always had meat, we did very well tha
t way, some people perhaps couldn't afford it as much as we could, that's not saying we were so well off but we just had that bit extra, with having - running a public house you know. Oh plenty of vegetables you see, potatoes and swedes and - swedes were 
v
ery cheap, after we left the public house I went on - we went on to a farm on the same - about two hundred yards away and - the man was selling these swedes, we'd get them penny each you see, my father'd, go on you can have half profits, so I thought I wa
s going very well in going round the village selling these swedes. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You had a sort of substantial dinner every day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, very good, yes. The pudding, we always had a - a rice pudding and Yorkshire pudding or - bread pudding you see, t
hey made bread puddings in those days, saved their old bread and - in fact - I mentioned to my wife, you never make a - of course I can't have it now I've got diabetes you see, I can't have too much bread, you never make any - oh, she said, I don't bother
. I said, well, bread we give to birds we could make three puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you have a drink then at dinnertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Oh I don't know. No, I wouldn't say - we had, no, we do now but - were never brought on - tea - drinkers - lunch time, dinnertime l
ike, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you have a special Sunday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, yes, that was always real - starting of the joint you see and that sort of thing yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What was your tea during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well it wouldn't be - just - bread and jam and - lu
ckily we used to get butter on it you see but some people used to get just butter or just jam but - and - a bit of cake sometime but - fruit and - custard didn't come out every day you see, just like a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your mother make her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 And jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, a bit, I don't know whether she'd make it all but she did make some, she wouldn't make it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did she bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Or vegetables, or make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, she'd make pickles, I remember because we used to -
 sandwiches, used to - you know, red cabbage or anything like that, yes, she did a lot of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did they make any wines or medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, I don't think she - she bothered a right lot with that. Of course they'd have their own con
coctions for - ailments you see which - old fashioned remedies you know. Brimstone and treacle and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Funny question to ask isn't it. Well even when left - after - he never did anything like t
hat like 'cos he'd go out and get it when he wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your father or mother grow any vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What - in the - in the - they would - one or two apple trees in - in the back. And he - he would do a bit but it was - very little be
cause - they used to bowl on the first lawn and then just higher up at the back there was a shed and bit of land, and I think they did a bit between them, the elderly - boys and me father you see, vegetables not - there was sprouts and things like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would most of the vegetables be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, they'd buy a lot you see. Well when he had the farm which would help you see, we'd get swede - cabbages and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about tinned goods, tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well I can't remember much of those at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you have any livestock, hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, we'd - we'd have a few hens I think too but - at the back, mm, not many but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well me father and - and the elder boy, well we children you see we'd run up and - you know, they'd say go and feed the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 hens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from anybody who did any poaching? Was there any poaching done round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 It's possible but I don't know of it, there was a - a wo
ods and the fields but - it wasn't what you'd call poaching, it was sort of never - never talked of like it is in some areas much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you remember ever seeing your mother have less of anything to eat so that the rest of the family could have more?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, she'd be a woman that - that would do it if it was necessary but - I can't think of her - having to do it, unless it was something special she - she'd bought short and she'd give way to us, you see, but not of necessity, you see - you see, it w
ouldn't be necessary because she - somebody just grabbed a bit more than they should have had and we got to you see and she'd give way to us youngsters, very good, a very nice lady that way mind you. Other than that I can't see a right lot of - but what I
 don't know - but up to eight year old I know - and I've heard the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 elder}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  sisters talk you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your father have bigger portions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, usually. Yes, but - never - he was never noted to be anything do to you know, well he naturally had more than the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were you allowed to talk during the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well, yes, but - not too much you see, we were brought up in the - sort of you've got to be seen and not heard you see and - we were very strictly brought up in that line you see. I would
n't say as strict as some perhaps but very strict you know and - you'd to watch - watch yourself or else you'd get one you see, she'd be a bit too - too much of it, went of it - overstepped the mark you see.
