\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well they're all hopeful aren't they, see, well do - a bit di
sappointed in of course in their family see going out, a bit disappointed in - the elder brother, he was next to the eldest but he was the eldest brother, he ran a bit wild you see, and - he - he was a bit - hot tempered and fighting, you know, he was alw
a
ys in bother you see. And - they had a bit of a difficulty, me mother and father like. Father was very strict on him and - see my mother was - batted him, not backing him to do wrong but sticking up for him a bit you see. But - eventually - he went to Ame
r
ica when he was - later on in life. He's a clever fellow and did well out there and died out there. But he wouldn't give in, me father being so severe, and being the first one you see, only thing was to keep him like that, down you see and - he wouldn't h
ave it you see and that's the - because I think later on in the family they gave way a bit more, to me father you see, but he - he wouldn't you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your parents bring you up to consider that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well, they 
brought us up to be mannerly to everybody you see. Manners - being - raise your hat to people and ladies and - all that and - they were pretty good that way, they - and - and - you know - don't say you know, he says, you've - he said, but don't say you kn
o
w because - you - you don't know everything he said, there's a lot to learn in life, he said, you don't know, he said, get to know, you know, he was pushing you that way you see, wanted you to get on you see not - not - of course you see, they could be am
b
itious for us - in those days because we were too young you see in the early days. But they're all just - but there was one thing about me father said is, now he'd only one brother that - when he got to age of - he got to go to the grammar school, I've to
l
d you that story, I don't know whether it was on the tape then but - about not being allowed - I couldn't allow to go sit for an examination that I would have passed easily, now there - there's one brother next to the top, he let him go to grammar school,
