ou know, like in the village you see. Later on like I got a bit older it was all running because I got to be a professional runner eventually see and - but I was always keen as a youngster running you see. Got always sport, much less - you know, but there
 
was nothing - nothing for - there was a common we used to play on, but - we hadn't any like running fields, we'd to run in anybody's field or - or you know and you know go a long way to get a place to run. Now they build them a big stadium in Keighley and
 
- but - I don't know how much father it's got, and they tried to form a - a local athletic club, less way they couldn't get enough members to form one, and there were we, you know, we'd have given anything to have a - something like that, but we hadn't an
ything at all, we just had to - just go and - into the fields, walk up Steighton way or anywhere round. Cinder tracks, I used to practice on the cinder tracks a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about Sundays, was that all taken up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Church usually. Yes, we were made to 
go you see. I - I - luckily I got - I got away with a friend of mine used to blow the organ and I used to go help him. At the back on Sundays. That was at - not all the time but I did occasionally, I said, oh, I'll come with you and - tonight Clifford you
 see and went - comics, reading comics you see, and he'd to blow - you know, the bellows at the back of the - the organ, it's funny but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you have special clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Special clothes? Oh yes, well - even Saturdays - at times we couldn
't put our - Sunday clothes on but we could perhaps put our Sunday shoes on, now when - although we - we - had - just nicely comfortably off, we weren't given a lot - some people that worse off seemed to get more clothes than we did, it was very - they we
re very strict. To }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 wear clogs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 and ordinary clothes - even Saturdays, we didn't always get - but we - got we were going somewhere specially, but then at Sunday it's Sunday suit you see, and Sunday shoes and your Sunday shorts you know, always Sunday you see.
 And these had to be kept then and put away specially - in the big chest of drawers and - and left 'til next Sunday unless there was something special in that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were you allowed to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 We couldn't play cards on a Sunday. 
And we're not - they didn't expect us - of course we - we - as kiddies we'd play football, we'd go away for walks and play - with the ball you see, but - you weren't - weren't allowed to play in the street you see. That was taboo. And - we couldn't - we c
ould never get to play cards on a Sunday, no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your parents think it was wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, yes - well you see, they couldn't think that because they had the public house and - and were working you see. You see, but t
hey - kept us - perhaps a bit more strict than what they - were themselves you see, well that's what it was, they do a thing, do as I say not as I do you know, that was - then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Your parents didn't go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Me mother'd go occasionally. My fa
ther - I think she went to chapel, but - me step-mother, me second mother, later on in life, she went to chapel and we went to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You were Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your father ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not much, no, no, he wasn't a church
goer. But mind you he wasn't - against religion naturally you know I mean - in some things he was a religious man if you can understand what I mean, he used to say - a fair minded man like he - he knew when he was wrong and - but if - very strict and coul
d be hard in some ways but on-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 The Sunday school that you went to, was it that had the outings, the field days that you went on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Went on those, yes, mm, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were there any other sort of social activities that the church or the Sunday school organised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well - it got to the time then I was - young in twelve, 1909, they formed a - Boy Scouts you see at the church, well that - naturally - was a great outlook for us you see and we - all the local boys enjoyed that wonderful you s
ee when they formed it at the church you see. We were getting out and going places you know it was - jolly good was that. Of course it just takes up that - period of your life when you - just wanted to do things you know and - yes, yes. Oh it was great wa
s that. Mm. Quite enjoyed the scouting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You didn't belong to the choir?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. No, as I said - they wanted me to you see but - and I didn't want to break off from the other boys I was going with, that's how I -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Yes, that - that - no, nothing like that. They - we used to go - one of the fellows we know, he was - he was - used to go on a Friday night class, young }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  class and we used to go you see, again they'd get me singing there at times like I'
d open up with a hymn you see and they'd fall in like, but I wouldn't join the choir you see, I - I'd do it for 'em then like, well the other boys would go at Friday night but they wouldn't - Friday nights, Sunday nights they were off and I'd have to go s
ing in the choir you see, so - I didn't join it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was there any other club organised by the church that you were connected with at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Cricket club. Was - we were - we were too young to get into the team you see but - well - we'd go and watch them you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was grace said at mealtimes in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, I don't think so. No, no, we didn't have them, but we just taught to say them when I was very young you see at night time. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Not seriously, but he was always a Conservative. But - he didn't - enter into them at - I don't think - may have been asked to - to put up you see,
 I've been asked twice to - to put up for local but I - he - I don't think he was really too interested, and I - I wasn't too interested really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you know why he was a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, whether it was his business }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 leanings,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  well when he went i
nto business I don't expect they - they're all - a lot of them are like that. You see, you grow up, some grow up and - father's Conservative, I'm a Conservative you see. I think his father had had a little business or something and - they could come up li
ke and - sometimes it follows through life, the generation after generation.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about your mother, was she interested in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I don't think so - she wouldn't have the time to - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 And she of course would have died before women could vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes, she died in - 1905 you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you remember your father voting in the elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I remember him later in life you see, before I got married you see, oh yes, he was pretty well - go to vote you see but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
18? Yes, yes, I remember him going during the war, because I didn't go away 'til - 1917, see I'd know him going then to vote you see and - I was nineteen then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 In some places people used to feel that they might risk losing their job or los
ing their house if they voted differently from their employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was your father ever under any pressure of this kind do you think,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, well you see it was a big firm and - he worked for you see and then it - being - working on his own.
 No, I don't think - he had any affect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was he actually a member of the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well he was a member of the - branch Conservative Club in Keighley. It was - Dalton Lane, it wasn't the headquarters club you see, it was the - one of th
e - because there were more of them then than there are now you see. More - Conservative Clubs you see, which have - have sometimes turned to working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  clubs now you see you don't get as many - Conservative clubs at small way like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did he ever work for the party at election times in any capacity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well naturally he'd put bills up in his window you see. But I don't know whether he would do that, I can't remember, because - well I don't know it mattered to him in that - where he was in that
 business but you see a lot of business men, they don't - don't themselves, they deal with everybody you see. Now whether he - it'd worry him you see, owing to being a - local you see and they'd all know him, being - and - and do you know there's - there 
is a lot of Conservative - Conservative Liberals you see they weren't - the power of Labour there is today, you see, and it wouldn't matter as much like then which it would today perhaps you see. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would your mother ever do anything connected with politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, unless she was asked to do something, a bit of a job you see, but she never put herself out, if somebody asked her to - help with 'em she might do - I've never - never known her do anything special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, I don't think so. Oh if - if he thought he could persuade anybody to vote Conservative he would do like, but that's all his point you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When your parents weren't engaged on doing their work how did they spend their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well both mothers was home birds, for - that - I don't know how to - start you see, what year are we in you see, 'cos - I'd three mothers - a mother and two stepmothers you see, it's pretty complicated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 We'll start off with your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 And then we'll leave reference to your stepmothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Stepmothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Until afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Later. Yes. Mm. Well you see, as my mother died at - when I was eight you see - I wouldn't know muc
h - about her really. But I know she was a real home bird you see. Had holidays, of course my father had to go away you see and left the - the elder - the two eldest sisters to look after the public house, that were a - a help then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did she have any interests outside the home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I can't recollect her - she - she may have gone to church occasionally but she - she saw that we went and I know that, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did she ever go out purely for the sake of enjoying herself can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, she - she had a sister and two brothers - that I think you get more - the - enjoyment was visiting them you see. She had two brothers, had two brothers that had - public houses, one at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 
Connolly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  and one at Skipton and she used to go there, and she
'd another sister that lived - another part of the town, I know - we visited them as children, that, so I know that. She used to look forward to that, taking us, the - the younger children you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What time did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well - whilst he was - locally employed you see, and we had the public house, he'd work and - be home, see they'd work - work the fifty-five and a half }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 hours}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  a week you see, he'd be home in the evenings perhaps - six o'clock we'll say, and 
the Saturday about - half past twelve. Now - I won't say he'd come home always you see he was a member of a - a local club not so far away, now he might, he was - just for a change you know call in there and - 'cos they like a - a drink away from their ho
me - public house you see, call in just occasionally there and you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When he got home how many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well - most of them I should say, with having his full - his - public house to run seven days a week, and -
 helping - my - at night, because my mother had been - had it all the day you see and so he'd - he wouldn't get out much, if he did it would be - perhaps the same as the - they do today that the landlord they have one break and it's their night out and he
 - he'd go to the local - club you see which he was a member of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 On this question you mentioned that he was a member of a working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 men
\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 And also you mentioned the Conservative Club at Dalton Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Is this one and the same thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, there were two. No, the two. Well he used to get into trouble - later on - he may have done the same, but when he married the - my first stepmother you see - I would be about ten then, he used to - he wasn't a - a man that - was - 
everyday drinker you see, he might - just occasionally have one, but he got - doing that Saturday coming home you see - and this got a little - just by the railway station which - there were no buses in those days, he'd call there and - he'd becoming home
 
at - half past four and then - not serious trouble but he got into trouble then you see. Because you see he worked away a lot for his firm too, and when he was away, same as they were working in Bradford, Huddersfield, or Halifax you see, getting to the s
tation you see and he'd - call in for one, well that one used to have about four or five you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 This was a fairly regular }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 occurrence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, it was just - his life you see. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your mother ever go out for a drink anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, I don't think so, she'd only go - no, she didn't go to any place like that. Well there weren't clubs in those days you see for women you see, I mean they weren't allowed in you know. But if he took her out you see naturally on holidays she'd -
 go in and have a drink, but she wasn't a drinking person you see. She occasionally - perhaps suppertime }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 we\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 have some - Guinness or something like that, but she - she wasn't a drinker. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not really. I can't remember him - being a sportsman you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Might have been occasionally but he wasn't a betting man, and he wasn't a gambling man. He - he was a very - you know - bit - I won't say a bit tight, a saver you know, he'
d - he wouldn't spend a penny where he could manage on a ha'penny. Only - when he went out you see he wasn't a - you know, they are - men are like that sometimes, they'll spend more than what - well it didn't apply in his case but I've seen 'em do it you 
see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, we had a local one in the public house, a branch. Was it the S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 k}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 ip}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
ers or not. And it - it's only about three since it - well wound up I remember and - most of the family were in 
it, you see, because it was - every Monday night in - well - next to the - and - I've told you about this before, sort of domed shape and it - it was always called the club room. Even at weekends when we opened it you see to the public it was always the c
lub room you see. Nice room too. And - we were all in that, it was all - co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
pers a week you see, and me brother - two brothers that died older than me, of course I was too young, they were in you know. Yes. Mm. Of course there all gone, there aren't many of those now, they were all more or less wound up weren't they. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Going on to your stepmothers and your relationship with them, you were ten when your first stepmother appeared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh wonderful, she
'd got a - you see there was - he brought three with him like, there was eight in the family. One had - gone away from home, when me - me mother died, in the lodgings and - and he'd taken three with him to the - one of me sisters. When he married again we
l
l it was three, there was - six - what did I say, eight - in with - eight, I was ten, and my brother fourteen, the other one would be about nineteen, he was a tailors apprentice, but when he got married again he came back home you see, you know, the elder
 
one, he came - the eldest of the four, and - went - on all right but with a lot of interference from the outsiders. This was the - the elder people - elder brothers and sisters, they got a big jealous of me stepmother, you know how it is in a big family, 
g
ot split up you see. And - and I'm afraid they got the youngest one, you know, she was only eight you see, well - they seemed to make a fuss of her and - I was - used to that you know but I was only ten I - I you know I - I wasn't being brought into their
 arguments you know, I thought oh - you know. They got my young sister in you know and it - it seemed to upset - other than it seemed to upset me a bit you see, she was a bit wayward. She's all right you know, nothing but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You mean they tried to turn her against her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Get a bit - yes, that's right. Although remember - me father had some property and I used to collect the rents for him but - ten I could you see, and - and - I called on me sister, she had a beer off shop, but so far off the public 
house that we had, and she - she said, well - one time I went in she said, oh, she said, how's the duchess? Well I had a - I went one sister that said, how did - did they say anything? They wanted to know how the duchess was going on, well - she must have
 
blown her top and then - at again you see, loggerheads you see. She shouldn't have said that you know but - youngster at ten year old you know, she - you know. Of course she'd only be about twenty-five, she was married anyway and her daughter twenty-six y
ou see. Mm. So I was in it next time I - I called you see. She said, you little devil, she said. But she - not - not really you know, it was all right, she - the next time I went she - they'd forgotten it you know. For telling stepmother what she'd said.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You got on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh yes. And funny later in life I - my youngest sister, she - she'll say it now, oh you, you're all blue eyed boy to me mother, well she meant the stepmother you know. Because I was the youngest then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You say that she had a daughter after she married your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, no, she had a daughter of her own when she married - me father. Yes. And - she used to come and visit regular. And I think they were a bit jealous of the outsiders, me sisters you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 
She could come and visit you know and all that you see, of course she was making more of her own daughter - well it's an old story now, I don't suppose there's much in it now as there used to be then. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 'Cos - they all seemed to go out and make their own amusements, it were more family life in those days, it and it - crop up more than it would do today. Yes. Of course it does today doesn't it, there's always something.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What sort of interests did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh she was a - bit religious, not serious you know but she a
lways used to be - she was Wesleyan, she used to go down to Wesleyan chapel, it was about half a mile away, and - she'd always go down on - Monday evenings, and on a Sunday, she used to go to service on Sunday. While we went to church, and - the - young o
nes that were at home, we went to church, she saw that we went to church. Me father did, me father - although he was not - not a bad fellow but he wasn't - churchgoer you see, didn't bother himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Had she any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, she
 liked her - when he was working at - he'd a few friends you see, there was about three or four - that worked - the - fitters are, you know fitting machines up for the - firms at Keighley you see, and he got friendly with them and I know he visited - me f
a
ther and mother and youngsters, especially the two young ones then, when I got twelve, going up thirteen, fourteen afterwards, he didn't bother coming with us you see, but - my younger sister two years younger than me and myself, used to go with - with th
e
 parents to visit these people you know. Sometimes - only time - naturally we would. And others were older, and - they had no children you see. But - comics and - quite enjoyed it going with them you know. Oh she was good to us. And - me mother, even me s
i
ster said she wasn't good to her, I don't know why, 'cos she was more strict, with a - a girl you know, if the - it - staying out too late and all that, they're scared for them and she be on her back you see a bit then. And she'd go tell her - her elder s
ister that was away you know, then - you know, they'd think they were killing sort of, and it was only - more or less looking after her for her own sake you see, yes. Oh yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Had your stepmother any interests quite independent of your sort of household that she'd developed earlier that she carried on with then?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. No, visiting with him. Going to the chapel. To the - mothers meeting perhaps Monday. And going to service on the Sunday evening. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 I don't think she'd any further - she'd - a good nei
ghbour next door, he was on the council and she was very, very friendly with her, and - next door, she was all right like but - she was a peculiar woman was the other woman, she didn't - make as much fuss of her you see, because she - she wasn't - somehow
 or other the type you know but the - the lady, Mrs Oxon, she was a wonderful person, I liked her. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
I've got a funny story about - can I tell this story? Her husband was a councilor you know, he's a plumber on his own, master plumber, and - my mother used to
 - although me father kept her a bit tight she was saving a bit I know, she used to - she used to buy butter, and she used to buy - Maypole margarine you see. And she'd mix it you see. And - Mrs Oxshott saw her, she said - my husband won't have - margarin
e
 in the house, won't have it in the house. But she said I - I'll try some - on him, so - she bought some, and she'll mix it you see and she said - and he was eating it and - always used to say - always afterwards he'd never eat margarine. He'd been eating
 
it all the time. Of course in those days - even same as, you know - meat and that, most of it's frozen, but if you bought cheap - cheaper frozen meat, people sort of looked - down on you a bit you know, you were - but it was done. I remember - my wife now
 
I was telling her a story that she wasn't in a good position because her father like he used to be - like drink too much you see, and - her mother'd say - she was a lovely lady her mother, I don't know why she'd marry him but - that's by the way, and moth
er'd say, now - fetch some - when you go into town fetch some margarine }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
- -the Maypole, but look around and see nobody sees you. You know. It sounds - funny now. Don't see you, buying marg - think nothing about it now do they, no. But they didn't want to
 make them think they were poor you see, so they didn't. She was but you - you wouldn't have thought so to see her like but - she was brought - she hadn't much money because he - well -
