\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 Redmond\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 in Leigh is a big store you know, with a big staff and all those days, he was manager there, manager at Barrow-in-Furness. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 
So they all done very, very well, you see but - the father was clever, but he - he thought the same way - he had a business as well,
 hairdresser - he had a hairdressing, he used to think all - all his - takings were profits you see, well those fellows didn't bother about bills to pay.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your stepmother take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, not really but she'd be like me fath
er you see, he was - they were always Conservative me father was. She was similar minded you know. And I don't think she'd be - like - the way she used to talk like a - I never thought she would be anything else you see, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You say you had a second stepmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was that later on in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Seventy, when he was seventy you see. Came to live with us you see for a period, and he got married again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Always well
, yes, always well, I liked them there was nothing - nothing - me eldest brother was a - he was the wild one of the family, you see. He'd go out - get in some - not serious like but - but he was always good to - I don't know, good to me. I remember him bu
y
ing me a - a watch at - and it was five shillings in those days I know that. Well a watch, five shillings was a lot of money, Ingersoll watch you know. Things like that you know. But they varied you see. He - he was good. The second brother, no, he didn't
 
- very rarely he did and the next one never did. Of course the one just above me well he wasn't in a position-to do it you see. But sis - but the eldest sister - she - she's about seventy-three and her husband died about three months ago, ninety-four. And
 
she was - he was strong Labour and - she used to - and give a ha'penny to her and she'd make it you know, do twice ha'penny you see, she was that keen you see, but - she'd never - give you anything but - I mean when you went you was always - lovable and -
 
made you welcome you see but - she'd - she'd nothing to spare. But me other sister, her that said - about - how's the duchess? She was very generous, she's living yet, she's in Warbank Hospital ill, she's nearly eighty-seven. She was very generous, and - 
we all think about one nephew - goes to see her now and takes her things. He said, well - you always were very good to me when I was a child and he's sort of paid her you know. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was there anyone of your brothers and sisters that you felt specially close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 The eldest in a way. Lilian. But and the other - they're both - I felt, you know, two of them, the one that's in St Johns now. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 As a child who did you play with, was it your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not much, you'd play with - we
ll - one older than me was four and a half years older than, me, well that was a bit of a gap you see. Well at home I play - me other sister like in games and whatnot. But outside we'd - it was a funny affair mind you. And we'd - play, we'd - this - knock
i
ng stones, I don't know what we - you - well I don't know how we used to say - this was duck and pay, you know, meant duck and pea, you know, you'd pile stones at one on top, you'd to throw stones at it and knock it off you see. I don't see anybody playin
g
 that, well they all do - rounders and - hide and seek, and then we'd a game called - dumb weights coming on. Have you ever heard of that? Dumb weights coming on. And - it - it - you'd a chap up against the wall, he'd be - holding the back up, and they'd 
a
ll get down with their heads down, like they do in a scrum, you'd get about four in a row you know, and then the others - other side - pick a side you see, and - they'd jump on one at a time, right over as far as they could get, so they could get all four
 
onto four. Ad - how - how - why it's called dumb weights, you haven't - when you got on you haven't to speak, you know, and - talking to - talking to speak. And - they try to shake you off you see and - if you clung on you see - you're all right, the vict
o
rs, but you see if you feel off you see it's - and you didn't jump on it was - I've never see it played now. And then there's usual cricket and football you see- And - we used to - there's been the alter, right on the moors from us, and we used to - form 
up sort of in - in the gang and get long poles, even like the scouts do, take food and go onto the moors, especially at holiday times you see, had some good fun and - and the big rocks you see and caves you know there. Oh plenty of fun.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was it neighbours children that you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Yes, yes, round about. Of course most of 'em - weren't quite as well off as we were but we mixed in and that. We weren't so well off but I mean - they, you could call 'em poor you see, there, you know, they were ver
y poor. And the houses round there were very - rough and some of 'em were dirty as well you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were you free to play with anybody you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes - they didn't - make any sort of - because they knew - if they went - if we went in like and sa
id a word that somebody had said outside you know up we got you see, me mother you know, she'd - perhaps pick us off you see. But you see, they were all - the parents would be customers, you see, most - most of the men, the fathers were customers at the p
ub you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you belong to any youth organisations, I think you mentioned the Scouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well that would be later in life you see. Yes - I'd be about thirteen I should think when they formed one at the church where I went to - that would be - tha
t would be after - me mother died and me father got married again because we lived straight opposite from the church you see, and - carried on with that lark three years, you see, scouting, I was a drummer in the Scouts, and - it was quite a good crowd we
 had. But not as well organised then as they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 As a schoolchild did you have any particular hobbies, keeping pets, collecting anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, we - we used to go in for the old books. The - Magnet and - Gem you know. And - hobbies, like there
 was always football and that - a runner you see, I was pretty good, I was - big lad you see, I was pretty good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When did you start to take up running, was that while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, I was at school, it was found out you see, I us
ed to run for the school you see. And football, I used to play football for the school. It wasn't as organised as I said before - on - on youth clubs again, but the schools ran league you see, the different schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you go fishing or go for walks or bicycling, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well - no. I didn't cycle because - couldn't afford a bike and - me brother had one once I - I was on that once or twice but - never took it up, nor fishing, no, no, we well we did it as kids - I thought you meant fi
shing you know in the serious manner. You'd all go - in the river round about to start with, splashing for tiddlers I expect, there was a beck run through you know - with a little jam pot with a string round you see, but that was always on the go you see.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 And you went for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, we went - of course as I said - we didn't - go on - we'd go up - up the hills you see, round the woods you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 As a schoolchild did you ever go to any theatres or concerts or music halls, cinemas, anything of that sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No. I remember now we have a - a photograph of the public house front - and that would be going back - six - seven - sixty-five years ago and - you see, you can see - the Silver King, that was one of the old drama things you know, that 
was on at the Queen's theater in Keighley, it's been pulled down - five years ago. But - we never went as children you see. That would be later in life that we - if I went up to a pantomime at Christmas time you see, that would be a - a great thing, we ne
v
er went to - of course there was no - no pictures until they came in first at the Mechanics, and there used to be a traveling - cinematograph - of course silents, that - came about - going back to 1900 - 1909, something like that when they came to the Mec
hanic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
, and they'd come round to the schools with coloured tickets you know, and - giving these out, you could - if you took one of these you'd get in for a penny, I expect if we went without one you'd get in for a penny but it was just getting up to go you
 see, penny and a pass we used to call it at the Mechanics Institute. Of course that was burnt out about - about five years ago I should think. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not much. I don't know whether it was a penny or a ha'penny or something like that you'd get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was that regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, always regular you see. Of course you could buy a lot for - a penny and ha'penny in those days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh I don't know, nuts and - and sweets.
 I tell you what we got, it's like - tree - twigs you know - licorice - and twists as you used to see them. Yes, and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 Spanish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 ribbons and - mint buttons and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 bull\rquote s-eyes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 and all such as that you know. But - but you see, when we came into - after mother - g
ot married again you see me - me - eld - next to eldest sister took over a - her husband was a tailor in - in the village and she took over next door a beer off shop, and I called there you see, always got a few sweets off her you see, I was lucky like th
at you know. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh I might have mentioned this before and - me first mother, she - she had a - a woman came in daily you see to help her you see, used to call 'em servants in those days you see and call 'em maids today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about if your mother was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 Well we'd two - the two eldest sisters you see they were - you see there's twenty years in - the youngest and the oldest. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well the one in hospital now si
xteen year older than me and the elder one - eighteen - ninety, yes, she's eighteen - eighteen years solder than me. So they always helped you see and - this woman coming in daily - you see, of course me father'd - stop off work then you see to help them 
out, unless there was a special job working away but - he could do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you remember what happened when one of your younger brothers or sisters was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, well you see I was only two you see so there'd be no one younger than me like that w
ouldn't enter into my life see, they was all older you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You mentioned that your mother's relatives were living near. Did father have relatives living near as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. But it's rather funny that - we didn't mix with them, I don't know why. 
What shall we say we knew of them see - I don't know, he sort of - chap in himself like, he didn't - but he - he - he went to his - his - my mother's - relatives, the two, that had - the pubs, naturally it'd be an outing to them and he could get a drink o
r two you see. That's probably what he'd do it for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 So your parents tended to visit your mother's relatives and not your father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 That's true, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about friends, did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well she was always friendly with a
ll the - neighbours, I've told you before about her helping people that were - drinking too much and - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But I meant close personal friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Only me father, I don't think she had - the second - or first - stepmother. She had the next door you 
see, and - and she made a few friends with the chapel people, you know, she didn't - especially -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would these be people who were not friends of your father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh that's right you see, because he - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 They were her own independent friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, he wouldn't be sort of interested in - he'd think more about his own friends than he would of - my mother's I think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did they tend to visit their friends separately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes. That's right, you see, me mother'd go to these chapel people do you see and me father - perhaps a night at the club you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about friends coming into the house, would the friends invited in be your mother's or your father's or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Mostly me father's, of course they'd - they'd visit toget
her, there you see and - they'd - they'd ask them back. Now in the case of me mother, she'd go on her own you see, if occasionally she'd ask them for tea well - you see, they might blow after tea you see before me father came in later you see. Afternoon t
ea and then we had high tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not aright lot, no, I can't remember - that - casual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about neighbours, were they ever invited in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 One at each side used to come in, yes. Oh and then
 there's one in another street, she got friendly with her, she came in a bit do you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your mother visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, she'd just pop in you see, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was that a by invitation affair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Casual you see, if they - you know. I know 
that - you see the women next door she never left any children you see well - she'd be popping in more or less to our house than we went to hers you see because - she'd come for news you see and - all - the family, we'd talk you see, especially later when
 we were in our teens you know, a nice person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
This business of people making their own amusements in those days, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well it was only gossip, work and - that, eating and - we were there so there was nothing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did they play games and make music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh they'd - no - not much, no. But they liked it that - that my sister that she'd play a bit but - me younger sister, but she wasn't like a - an expert or owt like that y
ou see, she was - used to just play the piano. Parents. No, they weren't - they'd enjoy it you see but - they weren't - wouldn't have made it you see. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did they play games with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, occasional card games you see, they'd play 
that and so on. Makes you wonder now I think if you - the - that the people are fed up or anything now, in the old days they just - resigned themselves to being what things were didn't they. A young person now they're - never satisfied are they, everythin
g laid on for them and now they're not satisfied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 We've touched on this question of some people being rough and what not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 And it being a poor area where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Could you tell me something about the community around there, the different sorts of people and their relationships one with another?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Mm. Well the next - the next - there was sort of a shop next door and they were supposed to be - just a bit - higher in the community. They had a sort of a - grocers shop a
nd - he was a - and a druggist you see, have his bottles of all sorts in you see. And he was - must have been doing very well because - he brought his children up to - schoolteachers and all that, of course they thought it was wonderful you know, a school
t
eacher in those days you know. And - and it - he was - he wasn't a drinker you see and - he'd spend his money on - educating his - family you see, they all - did pretty well, not - not in business, might have been in business two of 'em but - one of 'em w
a
s a druggist and about three of 'em were teachers, three of the - the womenfolk you see. And - of course my father just the opposite, he - his - one gone to grammar school that was it. We - and that was finish to it you know, he should have spent it on th
e others you see. But I was going on then and then - next door there was - they're houses you see, the - some were - nothing on the floors you see, some had a bit of matting you know. Stone }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 
floors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  in those days. And - some of 'em weren't - nice and clean and others were dirty, you see, you could - as you went round, with the other kids, they went in. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 And I remember one - at Back Row you know, that was very dirty house but - they - they used - she used to make - brown peas you know at Friday night and - cours
e we - brown peas in those days they always had brown peas, they used to come round - with a can you know, the fire underneath you see, selling them you know, dish them out, you'd go out with a basin and then come in and - penn'orth or ha'porth you know.}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Is this what we would call black peas in Lancashire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Maybe, yes. Yes. Ah. Mm. Same thing, yes, black and brown. And it was a - the name of this woman and he was a - he worked for my father when we had the farm, and that was a dirty house. And ne
xt door was very dirty. I didn't go in there once - about once when it was dirty. Of course ours was so clean you see and tidy you see. You notice these things even as a child you see, the difference that - and now some of them - these nice people round a
bout their homes were - not - well no doubt furniture you know but not carpeted or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 like that but - they were clean you know. Nice people. You see, we'd a mixture you see, you get that in some areas you see. And some were - couldn't care less you know and others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What sort of people would have lived in the dirty houses? Was there any common factor that you could put your finger on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, but squabbling or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 fights}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  I remember like - fight one - some fighting one house against the other, the - the lads you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about the adults? How did they get on together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh they seemed to do very well you know but - usual gossip and all that but - I don't think there was any - too much bother between them you know. They'd take sides in - in fights 
you know, not join in but you know - shouldn't have done this and he shouldn't have done that and this that and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 together}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 but - they wouldn't join in, I never saw any - women,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You mean commenting on the actions of the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Children, yes, tha
t's right. But you could tell a - some of them were badly clothed you know, we were always - just tidy. Perhaps we weren't fashionable but we still had always good stuff on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were some of the families definitely regarded as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh yes, yes, that's right, but there was a - it - you know, they'd go up in steps you know, rough - you know, very rough and rough and - medium and - nice and tidy and clean and - you know, you - you know - even my memory goes back when I was a 
child that - knowing different people, different houses but - I knew was - you know, right you see and - we would - you see a sack on the floor or something you know -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about the standard of living as far as food was concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh it would be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would that go in the same sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Yes, it was, yes - it was very low in some of them you see, labourer of course you know - those days you get as low as sixteen shillings a labourer you know. Mm, eighteen shillings. A pound was a good labouring wage you see. Mm. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 Well the - the mechanic's money'd be about twenty-seven shillings in those days, going back -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Thinking of the labourers, would they live in dirty homes, clean homes or would some be clean and some be dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes - I do
n't think that mattered so much you see it just depended on the person that - a man you see if he spent his money - going drinking he - and he wouldn't spent anything in the home, she got slovenly you see, now you get another that was - wasn't like that, 
he was - thought about his home more you see, he could make lower wage, it'd be better home you see, you - you couldn't say that it was on the account of money, I was because the - type of person that was - living there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you think that any of these different categories of people felt themselves superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well I - it always - is life, it's always - too - you - it's done unconsciously that - you - you know, you could see, we did you see, we went round, you just felt - you w
ere a bit better off than that and - but we knew - when - above town - town officials you didn't think you were up to them, all their sort of way, we would be you see. So now when I was young you see I'd think you know - worked in - town hall clerk - cler
k
s or something I thought how wonderful that you know. But you see now they'd be no better off than us you see. They'd be better off than perhaps the people that I'm talking about in the village you see of course but - it's just that thing you get in your 
mind when you're young sometimes. And we - we weren't brought up - me father didn't bring us up as - could have done, that was - you know - he could have - educated us more you know, but he wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I didn't quite catch that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were you brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775953\charrsid7673570 No, mother might say well - she might have said, leave them alone, don't - 
you know, you know, if they were very, very dirty see because - and vermin was rampant - in those days you know, you could go to school you see and - somebody'd - sat in front of you and he'd lean back, they'd be dropping onto your desk you see, oh it was
 shocking you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Of course you - everybody - very few got out of them you know, the - you couldn't - get rid of them you see. And of course - with a - I was - all right because - short hair it don't - but me sister you see, she'd to watch her regularly yo
u see, and keep her clean. Mm. But it was quite rampant in those days. Everybody Of course you don't see - I don't suppose there's much about now of that is there. You never hear much about it do you, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were there any sort of higher strata of society around in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, there's a - a detached house just higher up, he was an engineer - that's all, and he - he seemed to be in a better way with a detached house, big rooms you see. That was the only house in the neighbourhood you see. The adjo
ining works was a - it's there now, it was a soap works, well - type of soap works you know, soft soap and that, it was - oil works now, it's - local oil works now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Who would be considered to be the most important people in that district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well m
e father be - one of the most in a way you see, a landlord of the local pub, and the only pub there. And this - druggist I've been talking about. And this - engineer in the detached house you see, they would be about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you have any other professional classes, any teachers or clergy for instance living there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Or employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, it was a very - self-contained little place you know. No, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would there be anybody at all that you'd be taught to touch your cap to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. No. Never - never sort of made a practice of touching it to any - other than the females you see. No. Never entered -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Any particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not, you know, never - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Any particular women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, just were taught to do it to all - all of them you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would this include your immediate neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, I should think so, if you saw them out, but if you were on the doorstep you wouldn't bother you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But if you saw somebody who was say from one of these scruffier homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Yes, it - it - my mother would bring us up to do that you see. Respect them you see. She wasn't - she wasn't the type of person to - to - think like that, you know, not do with it one and not another you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What sort of people would you say went to the Church of England and what to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well in those days - remember you think - used to think on the chapel more as a - a non - teetotal, you know - they weren't drinkers like you - it was more or less if you went to church they weren't 
bothered about drinking you see. You see - if - I don't know - and the Catholics you see, well - they would think oh well they can do as they like because they can always get - absolved of it like when they go on the - doings you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was there a Catholic community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
There would be one or two of them, I can't just - I - I know I worked with a few of them when I got older, one in the mill as well you know I remember that. Of course the - kid we - kiddies we'd say oh well you're all right, you do as
 you like you see you know, kids. We met them at - at the mill where I worked you see. Of course that would be from twelve upwards to about fourteen you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would the congregation of the different types of churches be somewhat similar in its makeup, or would one be more better off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well - if you - if you go into the mill - type you see - the - the - church of England was - of course it was a - the mill I worked at was really the sort of the - I - Irish element you see, Roman Catholic, and they were very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 very poor you see. And - and I'm afraid we got the worst of those you see in this mill you know. And - but I - I was all right but it was the - just the - they looked upon them as poor you see, poor Irish folk you see. Mm. They were thought the 
weakest as well like in their morals as well. So that's why I say they used to say like oh you're all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, she just - she - no, she'd know she was a - good - B
ritish citizen I should say and - brought - and bringing her children up as - they should be brought up and - and the home was tidy, clean you see and - plenty to eat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well you see, he - he left it to her a lot that way 
you see but - if she reported anything like - as I say you see me dad - sort of - she didn't do any - punishing but she'd always - threaten - to - to - we would get punished if she said - she'd tell you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did he think of himself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, he never - he - he had never any big ideas like that but - he - he - security I should say, he just wanted to feel he was - he might give him a bit of standing in his own mind if he had - a bit of money you know, bit of mo
ney and some property that he - but he wouldn't - carry it - carry it too high you see, he wouldn't - make him think he was somebody too much, he wasn't that time but - he'd have it there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was it possible at that time for people to move from one social class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, well they would try to do you see as they got better off, not everybody - do, but some would, some if they got better off they just went - went - spend it - all on booze you see and - they wouldn't try to climb, they'd just - 
stop where they were. But there were odd ones that would you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you know anybody who did climb up, I suppose in a way your father did really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, that's right, well he just - saved his money and - you know, and - he'd always be - in the n
eighbourhood you see he was thought to be somebody you see and - he was pretty popular too, he was - hail fellow well met chap. Like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you remember anybody being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 referred}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  to as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 Well, I can when I'm going i
nto the - getting - up twelve you see then - the local - Sir Robert Clough, I don't know if you've heard of him like he - he used to - go on, if they asked him for anything, as kids, they were for forming a football club, we'd - the Scouting out for some 
money to buy a ball you see, he'd always be the first to give us something you know and he had a big - combing mill down Dalton Lane where we lived. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
And - mm - and you - you seemed to think - if you had a small business like - joinery and undertaken down be
low, you - you'd think he was somebody you see and - better off you see and - although today - it was run of things but - in those days when they were very - people were very poor, a small business like that that - they'd think they were - you know, someb
ody you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, yes. Mm. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 
We used to - you see, in the olden days you know we - we'd go - in - I'm going back now - we were very young - You know, we were scared of them you know
 because - they'd run after us and we'd - skittle you know and if - his cloak you know he'd nearly - if he got his cloak out you know he'd nearly send you flying off - off your feet you know, and - and - as kids we'd go round and - we'd call him, I don't 
k
now, you know, malarking, you know that word don't you, malarking is playing around - teasing people you know. And - we'd - tie a bit of a - a stone through some string and - from there to there, and put it on the window, on there you see and a - long str
ing and get away somewhere, then we'd start - tapping the window you see, and scare the - little things like that you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
But we never - nothing serious - trouble like, but always the - on the street you had something to occupy yourself with you know and 
he'd go round. And - I remember one time, I'd be about ten - we lived - me - me step - first stepmother. The fish shop at the street and about two streets above and - they'd always leave a sack of potatoes - outside you see, when we were coming home from 
s
chool you know. Oh potatoes, lets get one, you know, out of the bag. Anyhow - bobby came, saw us he must have been like - and he chased us you see and - I ran in the hone and this lady next door, she was a nice lady, she said, what's the matter? I said, b
obby chasing. She said, oh what have you been doing? I said, a - I took a potatoes out of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 sack}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
. They - they laughed to themselves you see, they'd say, get under the table quickly, be quick, get under the table now. And then he came in like, is that lad yo
urs about, you see. Well - I shouldn't say so, why, what has he been doing? You see. Told him like and - they must have been winking at him and I - what's he been doing? And - he told them like - see that he doesn't do it again else I'll take him on the S
k
ipton Road, that was a police you know. Of course I was under table you know, you were scared to death and - he went eventually, but tell him next time I catch him I'll - I'll see he goes on you know. But that was doing us - you know, you were too scared 
-
 that way, that's how it used to go you see. Mm. I never got into any trouble. Of course we'd - we'd go round - sometimes for apples you know, if - if you'd get one - get a couple of apples off a - tree you know, you - you got to those, you weren't really
 - bad things but we used to do them you see.
