\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did he treat people do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Who's this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 The policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh the - the norm - you know, the - they used to watch - now, if they got a bad case and stealing and all that, real steali
ng you see naturally they were after them and - caught them. And - they were scared that - the kids were scared of the police you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 
Although they - they had to - they could cuff you, you see without - getting the mother going to police and having it up - Member of Parliament you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
But nothing like that, it was just - you'd got to - and parents accepted it you see. They didn't bother, they knew - as a rule. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 
I remember one lad getting sent to reformatory he wasn't in this district, he was next - next d
istrict, but he was a - a proper wrong 'un you see, you do find 'em you see and he got sent to - reformatory school they used to call it, what they - a remand home now is it they call it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Reformatory school that was it. And then it looked very bad for - all the parents in those days, you see it seemed worse than it did today you know, oh it was shocking it would be - sent to a place like that you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was there any rowdyism in the streets there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not a right lot, I don't remember. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 Only when - I 
know there's once - Mormon preacher - they came, Mormon preachers you know, and I hadn't to know what they're all about you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
I got it somehow you know and - they have as many wives as they want you know and - I know they - they came to this little vill
age you know. All the women came out and they were booing them along the street. They thought we aren't going to be - have that coming here like. A chap having more wives than one. I remember Mormons and - tell you what used to come round - a chap came ro
u
nd with an old bear, you know, and if you'd sing to it it'd dance you know, collection and that sort of thing. They were - wonderful to us you see to see a thing like that coming round. And there was a German band coming, four or five of them and - us kid
s and - something out of the ordinary you know, came around now nobody'd take a damn bit of notice would they, just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was booing the sort of most people did to show their disapproval of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, or - or the - I remember this - there weren't any - squabbling or owt like you know, listen to them - booing and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 There wasn't anything that would come under the heading of rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Violence. No, there wouldn't didn't do anything to them. 'Cos perhaps again it come back to the old - w
e were scared of the police you know. They were more scared of the police you see I think in those days like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When you were at the Shoulder of Mutton was it your own or was it rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, they all belonged to them - we just - it was ours - to -
 to make and do as we liked with, but - it was rented off them and sell their beers you see. Mm. It's more or less like that today you see, unless you have a free house and somebody buys the building you see. They're mostly owned by the - the breweries yo
u see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Can you remember anything about the relationship with the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was the company a sort of a good landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. Yes, it - would be - it was only death of my mother that we went - came out, we'd been in - in there about th
irteen years and we'd had - another public house as well in town, and went on a farm. But - he got on all right, I remember now even the name, that's going back a lot, Mr Wood. He'd be the manager for the brewery you see and that. I remember Mr Woods comi
ng. Managing and - naturally }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 he\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 - when he came he'd - some sweets or something for us you see and - same as a - present day you see if a - brewery manager comes - if a traveler comes into a club you see well he won't you'll just play around you see and - 
oh well - they've always bit of money to spend you see and naturally - we kids came in for it you see and looked forward to him coming you see. And buy some sweets.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you ever at any stage feel that your parents were having a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No. That never came into ours, no. 'Cos we knew you see 'cos as a - as a child even - eight, nine, ten, I used to - go up the hill top with - to help - for - we'd four in the village, newly built ones and - two at the top of the hill, Thwaites 
Brow, it's right up top hill now but - I used to go up there as a child and collect the rents. And I did it right up to being married. Living at home you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Before you went to school were you given lessons by either of your parents or anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, no, it - we'd go at five but - we'd be - pretty well educated in the way we got plenty of - of books you see, we'd get - we did very well on that, you know, it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Plenty of books in the home you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, and little books where - you k
now, b's and p's, you know, alphabetic in - pictures. 'Cos I should say - we'd be a bit brighter with running about, running to - where the men were that talked to you and all sorts you see. More - education in that way I mean you know, you wouldn't be sh
y or anything because they'd treat you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When you first started school what were the hours, what time did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I don't think they'd be - much different as I think - the same as they are now. I don't think they was much longer, or very little l
onger if they were because - I know the first school we started at - five and went - three years, to a little - call it a board school, a little school, you know below the village and - then went on to a - bigger school. Only that - that was about - a mil
e and a half two miles away. And we had to walk it you see, we'd set off early to walk all this way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 That was to the bigger school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, and we'd to walk it back at lunch time for lunch. You know, it - we'd to do it four times a day you see at ei
ght year old, it was a long - long way you know, because they - they're putting buses on now and all that but we'd to - tramp it. Occasionally we'd stay - we know there was a - a little coffee house not so far off the school, we'd - take sandwiches and go
 in there and get - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 penn'orth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  of tea you see and - stay occasionally.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When you went to the infants school you'd go home for your lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, wasn't so far away see for that. Half a mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was the second school a board school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Y
es, a big - they've gone there 'til - 'til they went to the mills at - well it - it in those days of course it - used to go sooner when before - years before me brothers had been at eleven. But I don't know me eldest brother when he went possibly at ten. 
Then I went at twelve and - worked half time in the mill and then - went full time at - thirteen. See we do fifty-five and a half hours at - at thirteen year old see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When you were at school were they both mixed schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes. Together in the classes, yes, oh all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, I - oh I used to like it because - I like company and I - used to like it - the playtimes used to get breaks about quarter of an hour you see. Enjoyed it because - play football a
nd games. And the - the lessons weren't too hard for me you know, that would appeal to me you see 'cos some - some of them you see - didn't like it because it - it - more hard work for them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you like it at both schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about the teachers, how did you feel about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh yes. I shouldn't say this but I think got on very well with them with being pretty - pretty good you see like. Of course they ran the football team and I played football and ran for them you 
see so - I got more intimate with the - with the men teachers you see. And - lady teachers well I - got on all right with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, used to watch you, you see, if you didn't behave you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
They were strict on things like that, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Yes, yes. Oh it isn't often I remember being late, usually - there on time you see. You didn't like keeping in for ten minutes afterwards or owt like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were they concerned at all about the way you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, I - I never - have anybody - they may have pulled them up occasionally, you know, but - I don't think they made a right - strict ruling on that you know. And - and I must have f
orgotten it quickly because the - the - when they got outside it had all gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You'd be kept in school. I don't think they gave you lines or anything like that. Them sort of thi
ngs they do now, they'd only just - kept you in, because - some of them - would have bits of jobs to do you see and - if one teacher's staying back for do work you see you - you was told to stay. You'd sit in her classroom or stay in there with her you se
e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did they have any other form of punishment at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, we got caned, the cane. The headmaster used to came us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not the ordinary teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, we'd go to the headmaster and he'd give you a real sting across the - middle o
f your - palm you see. I should say it was - it wasn't just a cane it was - lead - centre was lead. Of course it was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was that for more serious offences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Not too serious you know, if you'd been misbehaving in class and - you know had got
 caught doing it again you see. But - you didn't worry too much about it because it was only done with you see. But I told you before I - most thing that worried at home with mother was sending me to bed. That was more punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were girls punished the same way as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
I can't think that, I can't remember the girls being caned. They may have been but - now you mention it I - I can't recollect girls being caned. Kept, yes, mm. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was there any standing out of the class or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, I've seen that done you see. That shame you a bit you know, stop there, yes, I've seen that done. I can't remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 having}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  to do it myself. But I've seen it done, I remember it occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was the punishment in the first school the same as in the second one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well I mean they must have been lenient or we were all good because I never remember in the first, up to eight being - punished. Of course you'd be - you - you - perhaps send a note - home you see if you were really - t
oo bad you see - to your parents you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your parents show any interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, they always wanted to see how we were gong on you know, always interested in you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did they visit the school at all or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I can't - I can't remember that at all, no, in olden days. No. Can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did the other children come from similar types of home to yours or were they from the community round about, rather mixed homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh mixed you see, they - with
 the second school you get them - from all - classes you see, I mean - well there were right low and - middle classes you see. Their father's be cobblers or - farmers and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 The second school was further away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, mm, a bigger school. About three or four times as big.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 So it would be a bigger range of types?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, they got - yes, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did the teachers single out some of the children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did they what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did they single out some of the children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
I can't say that they did. You're all to - you're all there, and - and - they'd only single them out if they were backward, backward perhaps, but they didn't specialise on - any one that g
ood at so much and - to bring him on further you see. But they may concentrate more or an - a backward one you see. Get him going more.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were there any gangs or groups in the schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well - yes, but not - serious you know. You - you'd gang up m
ore with your own neighbour - hood you see, you sent to school you see. You'd have bits of squabbles but it - it never got very serious. In fact I remember one - there was a - a - not far, the big school, there was a very low area, pulled down now - there
 
were a few from there, I remember once - used to be - used to get playing football cards you know and - get - buy five in a packet you know and - you'd - one you couldn't get you see, there were prizes given, one you couldn't get you'd to wait and wait an
d
 - hope you're lucky to get it some day. But this lad had told me he'd got it and I'd - he wanted threepence for it. Well I got one of me brothers to give me threepence, so I gave him the threepence and got the card you know, even in those days there was 
- of course he - I mean, it's funny, he often got into the courts later on in life, yes, so it was there with him you see, of course be - being brought up in that area and it was - his upbringing and it's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were there any of the children who seemed left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, I can't think I do. As I say they were all those types that - struggling through and - didn't like school. They put up with it and - made best of it, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But at playtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Playtime? No - very few, they - they'd 
sort themselves out you see. Even like - sort themselves out socially, in a way you see, you see - so and so sort of and - so and so's daughter you see, they sort themselves out - he was the chemist and he was so and so and you'd see them in a way I mean.
 
But - not all the time, but it - it - it was there you see, but - and - and - and they'd sort of mix with you as well do you see sometimes, get in a little clique of their own do you see. Mm. When it came to the sport and that - things like that, all toge
ther you see. They were more or less making their friends and sorting themselves out in the different - cliques you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did anybody accompany you on your way to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, no we'd trail on ourselves. A distant relative of mine lived not so far 
away and - you see we didn't - when we broke away from the junior school, we went to this bigger one we thought it was better you see for us and - there was one, a church school, a lot nearer you see, in the church, about a mile away, this was two miles a
way, and - we preferred to go this one, these - the two of us used to walk over two miles to - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You left at twelve, you became a half timer at twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Worker yes, half time at school and half time in the mill, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was that a week of mornings at school and afternoons at work, alternating with a week work in the morning and afternoons at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, afternoons - that's the - that's right, one - one week we were work the morning and - next week we worked the afternoons all like
 that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What happened about Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well when you're on the mornings you - you - do six you see. You do six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Before you actually became a half timer did you ever do any little part time job to earn a bit of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, I didn't do any paper round or anything, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Your half time job was in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was this a weaving mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. Woolen spinning. Spinning mill you know. Worsted, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What did you actually have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 First job was - w
ell when the first - the bobbins on the spinning thread were full you see, they'd stop the - the machine and we'd have to put - lift off - the full one and put the empty one on you see. And it was - quick - you could do - you know, you - you got right exp
ert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you do that the whole of the time that you were a half timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No. No, you got a - next job was - setting the bobbins on the - on the frames you see. Boys did that you see, yes. On the rails you see which you - the empty bobbin. And the -
 the next job after that was taking the - the full bobbins off you see, there was - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 changing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 the bobbins, that was doffing, and - bringing the - empty bobbins and putting them on the rails. That was setting. And then - taking off was taking off the full on
es you see like and there was three grades. And then the next one, well there was only - one in a room about - sixteen machines - they call you a jobber lad, you had a bit more money for that. And your job - oh that was - varied you see. First thing in th
e
 morning - you'd to go round and - all the - oil all the - the rollers, well it - it used to - in the wheel you know, you'd had a little can with oil on and a little brush and you - you go around all frames you see. You see, it was a - sixteen frames and 
t
here was about ninety, we'll call it a hundred on each side, that was two hundred sixteen times, three thousand two hundred was it. You know, you - of course you - you're just dipping it in you see. Of course you are supposed to have done it and - all at 
t
he same time you see, you do that first and then - you'd do a - I'll tell you what you'd do, if a - you were taught - if - tapes run tapes round to - make those run round off a big cylinder in the middle, it won't be like that now, and - you had a little 
s
ewing machine and you - you sewed them, if they broke you see, sew them and put a piece in, like a join to make the tapes and then - put it back on and set the machine and off you go again. Oh and then we had to look after the - well pretty well to - clea
n
 up a bit too for the overlooker, you - sort of you - next to the overlooker, the man that run the - the - these set of frames you see, and then at - break time, breakfast and lunch you see, take all the cans down, all your - all your workers in that part
 of the mill, take them down to the boiler house and filled up - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 big round}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 cans, they had cans there, bring their own tea and sugar and milk you see. You would - they'd put their tea and sugar in and you'd take the cans down to the boiler house, fill th
em up for them, for their break you see, they'd bring their sandwiches. That was the top job you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 That was while you were half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, that was - to the full, that - when I left you see. Half time you were just on doffing you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 And then you went on this other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Gradual - uplift, shilling or sixpence more you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When you started full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 As a half timer how did you get the job, was it through your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, the parents, you 
see me father used to go round all these mills, working you see, he know them all you see. So he started with the best mill first. And it was just at the time you see it was 1909, and there was very quiet and - a lot of lads couldn't get in some of the mi
l
ls. I was lucky, I - I got in, you see I went to three - places, They give me the nicest places first. He said, well, there's only one, he said, that's Copsey he said, but it's a bit rough. Well - I had to work you see so I went there you see and they set
 
me on and that was that, and I worked there - two years and then - I don't know if I've told you this story about how I went over - yes. Yes, and I went to a littler place and - I was just taking off there and I got a shilling more wage and it was a nice 
clean place and - I just struck better and I got the job and that was finish of the mill..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 As a half timer did you feel that the time you spent in school was worthwhile? Or did you really not benefit very much from it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, I don't think you settl
ed really. If you'd been - to the mill in the mornings you see, you'd start at six o'clock in the morning and work - long }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 hours}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
 you see, six hours. Well - tired you see and - well - you see, and some weren't as fit as me you see, they'd be more so you see 
and - I - well you - you didn't get down to it so much you see. You - you would do it you see. And then - in the morning when you went the mornings to school, you - you'd be thinking about going to work in the afternoon so - I don't know that it did any g
o
od or not. It would have been better to have started them at - twelve on a full time you think you know, to get the same - of course - the wages weren't so high for the parents in - most cases and - they wanted them to be earning to help with the - especi
ally with a big family, you see, they depend a lot on the first worker, especially to help the family - along.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
From what you said before I gather that looking back you would have preferred to have had more schooling, but at the time you weren't particularly bothered? Is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Yes, that's right. You see - I was - you know, you didn't think ahead in those days it's later in life and with father not being - one that - would - make me you see like - I - I just floated a bit you see. Of course -
 my stepmothers - were - she - she got - she was - that way, she got me going to the evening classes you see, although when I was working fifty-five and a half hours you see I - I'd go to the evening classes three nights - two or three - two hours, and la
ter it was three - two and a halves, and - you'd do your home - home - home work as well you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How old would you be when you started going to evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Straight away at thirteen. Thirteen. Thirteen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was that for a City and Guilds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No. Similar. We got certificates, upstairs, funny that, they're upstairs. Shorthand typing and book keeping, I - I got the first two years from that, from the evening classes, certificate you see. Mm.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I thought maybe It'd be a spinning course that you'd go on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, seeing that - that me mother wanted - to go into an office you see well it was - all right for me, shorter hours than starting at - at six o'clock, I was starting half past eight. Or washing overalls if I went into engineerin
g. Yes. Easier for her both ways. Anyhow - it - it worked out all right. I wasn't right keen because - I was shocking writer and I haven't much confidence in myself being - clerical worker you know with that, it's funny but - I won't say I'm a good writer
 now but I'm sufficiently good. You know, some people say I'm all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You mean - ordinary elementary school? Oh yes, naturally you see. The - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 
arithmetic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  what you call mathematics today, well that - you see, smartened me up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 And from your evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well yes, fair - I wasn't as attentive later on as I should have been but - I was holding it gradually you see, went on 'til I was about seventeen you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How long did you actually stay in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Two years and nine months. That's - a - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 year half}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  time and - a year and nine months full time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 In 1911 what would you actually be doing, would you be a jobber in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No - I - my last job was a - setting, and 
- the last place I worked at you see, I worked there about six months, that's all. At the end, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 At the end of 1911?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, I was - setting - when I - before I left to go to the office job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You worked in just the two mills?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
I started for - first I think it was about - oh, half time - it'd be about - four and threepence - in the afternoons and about four and nine or five shillings in the - for the mornings, something like that. Five shillings, four and threepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 And when you started full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Full time, I think I got nine and six, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you feel that that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, in those days it seemed all right to us you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you give the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
They took - took it all you see. Oh yes, there was not - in the - in the usual doings you - you did it 'til you were twenty-one, gave it to your mother. I didn't because I - I got a lot more money when I was eighteen like, and - I kept myself, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Before then when you were giving the money to your mother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 presumably}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  it would go into the household?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, and we'd just get sixpence spending money or something like that, ninepence or a shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 While you were working in the first mill how did you get on with the other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh all right, yes, mm. A lot of 'em - their - their standard of home life wasn't the same as I had you see. There was - some rough ones you know like, very poor and rough. Their mor - mo
rals weren't so good either some of them to - even when they're young you know. Shocking some of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did they treat you as a half }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 timer?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well they were very strict some of the overlookers you know. You know, they'd - they used to - they ha
d a - a wooden stick with a long - flat piece of leather on about this big you know and they used to dash the floor up you see - in - and - down and wool used to come off it when it was being spun, they were clearing all the passages up to keep it tidy, w
e
ll it was only going under the machine. But if you're a bit talkative and - and dodging and - they know you're talking instead of coming and rushing to next machine to - to - to start doffing the other you know he - he'd give you a smack on your btm with 
this stick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did you feel that the employer treated you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
The master of the - oh well luckily I was all right, he was a - he was an oldish chap you know and - they knew I'd - gone through the place like for those two years and - they got to kno
w me you see and - and I think they'd seen like I was a bit - brighter and - wasn't as rough as some of the others you see and - it's a wonder - that I haven't stayed on in the - mill like and gone through it you see. But - I never did, I got to this offi
ce job. But the old man, he - he used to come out and he always stopped and talked to me you see. A nice old gentleman. Had something to say, how are you going on? Do you like it here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Was this the second mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, the first one you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What about the second one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well I never saw - it was a - a limited company, never saw anybody only the overlookers you see. That's all. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well I took it in me stride, it didn't bothe
r me. I could do it you see, and - could do it better than the others you see, I was faster doffer than they were and - and - I felt sorry sometimes for the - the girl - the girls you know and - you know, at twelve and - and they weren't - they weren't as
 
big in those days and perhaps weren't as well - nourished you see, they looked very frail and - yes. They were children you see and - twelve you see - not half as good as they are now you see, with the milk - free milk and all that, nothing like that abou
t was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 So in 1912 you went on to an office job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 It - what - you mean - the firm I worked for? Well it was a - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 
rust proofing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  firm, you won't remember the old - set pot - washing coppers, yo
u know, they were cast iron, that they used to - set in brickwork and have a fire underneath. Do you - do you know? Yes. Yes. Well we used to - we used to buy them from Scotland these cast iron round - pans like a big - bowl, and make them restless, it wa
s
 a treatment we had - two furnaces or three furnaces, heat and stream you know, it - get them to a certain temperature you see and then put steam into the furnaces, and it sort of put a film a blue film onto the - rough iron and kept them rustless, so lon
g
 as they weren't scratched too much, so it's flat. But they carried on all right, they were rustless supposed to be because - soap you see - continued soap with them'd help to help this film on you know unless it was a real - crack or something it - you k
now, it'd last a lifetime you see. Year and years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 So you went to this firm to work in the office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Office, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What did you do when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Well start - first job was addressing envelopes you see. Bits of jobs
 like that and making notes out and - going to the post and - all - and - and - then - oh letter pressing. This is interesting to you perhaps. You see we'd no typewriters in those days and - we'd - write - with some - write the - letters and - well I woul
dn't but two of the two partners, they'd write the letters in this copying ink you see. And then we'd - get them together at night, all they'd written you see, then we had a book with tissues in. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 And - we'd some - a - a - a very thick pad like plastic under
neath it, and - we'd - put that underneath this tissue and then we'd a brush - a - like a - whitewashing brush you know, and we'd wet all this tissue, and then we'd - put blotting paper on, to take the wetness off, just so that it was damp, and then we'd 
lay - the letters - on top of this tissue, then put one of these plastic things - on the top of that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Then get the book, and put it in this press. And it was like - you know - I don't know whether you've seen them - have you seen one of these presses? Press
ing a book you know, handles at top and you pull it round to press it. And - and leave it in just a bit, and then you'd fetch it out and then - you'd have the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 copy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  of the letter on this tissue, you see, you'd be careful though you hadn't to - get it too we
t or else it'd blur all your - then you - you'd be in real trouble you know, you had to see that you - got the paper all - after you'd wet it, you see, copy paper, just put it in and - turn it slightly to get it - just damp you see. Then you'd a copy in t
he book of these letters he had sent out. That was your last - job at night - the office boy to - mm - of course I mean it was serious if you -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You didn't work as long hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh no, you see it was the ordinary - about - half past - half pa
st eight to half past four, two fours, eight and - Saturday would be forty - forty-three and a half you see, that was easy against fifty-five and a half, twelve hours less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What were you paid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh seven shillings. Spending money down yes. I
 got a shilling before, I come down to a ninepence, but luckily I was fifteen about three months after and I got nine shillings. But - I was in the middle of the scale you see. I did - I waited 'til I was - sixteen 'til I got eleven shillings. I don't kno
w
 whether it was thirteen at seventeen, but - but when the war started you see in 14, and then there was three of us in the office you see, the first one went in the forces. Straight away, and then - and then another went. That left me you see, of course -
 
they gave me - twenty-three shillings when the last one went, well that's a lot of money at that - and then a few months after gave me thirty, well - it was a lot of money for an eighteen year old you see. But you see I could do - any job at eighteen in t
he office then you see. The books then you see. 'Cos - you see, they don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Were you doing the accounting and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Yes, Yes, I'd do the books and - oh - then one of the partners did the cash book, but I did the ledgers and - da
y books you see and - sorted invoices but we had a - one - one of the chaps that went, we had it - is this interesting to you? Oh. One of the - chaps that went, his wife came into the office you see, and - they hadn't been married long, and then - when th
e
 other one went - the boss's daughter came in you see. One of the bosses, one of the partners you see. Then anyway I went - the other daughter came in so it finished up with - the partners two daughters and - and - wife of the one of the chaps that had go
ne out of the office you see. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you get called up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well - only - with trouble with me eyesight in those days and - I - Lord Derby's Army you know, it came out you could sign on, they'd call up when you were of age, but to show you wore a - 
or something like - Home Guard did and - this band on your arm, khaki band and - and nobody pulled you up you see, they didn't - white feather you or - you'd signed on, you were waiting to be called up you see. Anyhow I went on to our - I was nineteen and
 
they called me up and called me to Halifax and - said - well - we could keep you on as a clerk. Oh I said, I might as well clerk at home. He said, well - thirty shillings a week you see so I came back you see. Worked on, and then - I went another nine mon
t
hs and things were getting serious, they wanted me so - well they wanted everybody in those days, that was early - early 1917, so I went - up to Halifax again. Went to the board and it was just my eyes again and - I got to the Commanding Officer that were
 just checking them all at finish, who - said it could have been B - B1 but they gave me B2, and - B1 was infantry training, not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 airborne}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  but - B1, that was down at Brockton, in the midlands, I thought - go on, he said, it's - go on and so he let me through
 on B2 and I was at Blackpool next day you see in the RAMC so - and I finished up in the RAMC I think we - 'til the end of the war. I went abroad. They wouldn't send me abroad, I - applied to go on hospital ships but they didn't - they wouldn't have me an
d so - that's that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 While you were with this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 rust proofing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570  firm, how did you like it there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Well I was scared at first as I told you about - I was a poor writer and - and - we got - not being to the secondary school, I hadn't the confidence of s
ome - with that you see, but - mind you there was fourteen applied for the job, and a lot of those from the grammar school and all, that was from the grammar school, but I got the job. I don't know whether they thought - of course these two certificates h
elped you see. And - I don't know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you gain confidence once you'd started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Gradually, yes, from the boss you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How did the boss treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh very well. You see, but - one of them was a local - oh he was the Mayor of Keighley l
ater on. Oh he had been the Mayor of Keighley, and the other one was - little stock - stock key chap like - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10251023\charrsid7673570 K}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
ing Edward with a beard on you know. And he liked his whisky you know. But he - he was funny - if - there was any mistakes made you see - you know,
 he'd be doing - going so - he'd say, oh yes, I remember, that was when I was away. We knew it wasn't so, you know - it just feel off his back it was so funny, like when he was away when that mistake occurred. He never took blame for anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How long did you - did you go back there after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Yes. Yes, mm, straight away, I was discharged - funny during the war, with running I'd - during the war they said that my heart was bad - they discharged me, when I was twenty-one I think, and - they g
ave me forty percent pension, well they knocked it off and dropped it - twenty - and then they knocked it off in two years, and I went back there, and funnily - I went back and - now then just have thought more of me than - the fellow that had the account
s, I was the lowest of the three you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 
That's before - I was a youngster, and - they thought more about me in the accounts than the other fellow, he wasn't really - brilliant at all, so they made it to me, I felt a bit uncomfortable, let me carry on with
 the - head you see and - book keeping you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Yes. It was a bit unfortunate for him but I couldn't say I won't, I mean in business in life, if you're better than him that's all that matters. Now the middle one, he got - he'd had a commission had that one
, and he - he got out and - prefers travelling you see so - that's how it worked out see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 How long did you stay with that firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Been retired - I worked over fifty years with them altogether, since starting to retiring, over fifty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You never moved on to another firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. I've - been retired eight years now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 
I got to like accounts and - you know, and - balancing and everything and working out - you see - I worked 
it 'til - they weren't accountants, well at least these two partners - one died and - chap that came in had married his daughter, then he got to be managing director you see, well he was a - M.SC. but he was a schoolteacher type but he - he hadn't the gri
p of accounts that I had so I gradually grew up with the firm, it grew so big you see, you see when I went with them there were only twenty-five people and we were paying about thirty-five pound a week wages. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When I left there'd be about two hundred and fif
ty people and - about three hundred and fifty thousand a week in wages I was paying you see. And you see - I'd worked systems up during the period on the accounts you see. I wasn't a qualified accountant but I - I was a good one because - when I retired a
ll of the - the staff and everybody said, you know - always knew the accounts - how we stood and what we'd done, before the accountants came in, he said, Sam always has it pat for me you see I could tell you see, and we'd so many departments. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850101\charrsid7673570 We started in 
Hamling, Peter Street, Hamling, you know Peter Street Hamling, we started that thirty years ago, forty years - 1930, he did, this - MSc and he - we built it up into a big concern you see.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No you see, that's - training was automatic - it wasn't - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 On the job training really wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, that's right, because you started at a lower wage and that was accepted, you started at a low wage because you were lear
ning that job you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you belong to any trade union or organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, no, I've been asked to join like but - the clerical - you know, in those days you see, just after the war I think but - they weren't strong and I never bothered and I knew I was all right with them and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you feel that the employers and the workers had the same outlook towards the business and the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, well it was a family - family business you see and - and - they were very good, they were - with the
m you see and anybody wanted to speak to them the managing director he could do, they'd just come in and ask, yes, come in. If he was a busy man naturally he couldn't but - and it was - ironed out, there was never any trouble at all. Sold out last year an
d - there's been trouble since, it's a big combine, London Midland Industry bought it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you feel that there was divisions of interest amongst the people who worked there? In the early days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. You mean - in what the staff - in their socia
l activities. Oh yes, there's some we - religious and some wouldn't be and - some were musicians and some weren't, it was a right mixed crowd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 People say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that that was so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Oh I knew of it, yes, I mean - a labourer you see is - and there's such a big gap in the wages you see, than there is now, some of the labourers now earn more than some of the craftsmen I should think don't they. You see, whe
n you got down to the seventeen or eighteen labourers wage - and you got up to twenty-eight for a - tradesman, well, that difference was a lot of money wasn't it. You see, because - out of that seventeen shillings he'd to pay his rent hadn't he, well it w
a
s five shillings a week or six shillings, six for the - mechanics wage for rent you see. Well it was a more average - it was more of six - like five shillings out of seventeen wasn't it, it was a struggle you know to find. You might lay a four shilling re
nt out you see, that varied from -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You mentioned about having a shore when you were in the mill,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 About having a share.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Must have been someone else. We weren't on any bonuses or anything at the mill. At all no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 There was no profit sharing or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, no, no. Mind you - it may have been - in the business I left you see were on bonuses, the staff and - the - bigger end of us were on big bonuses, big percentage, and we do - when the - enamelling a bit - you k
now you remember these all night burning fires that came in don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 This is more recent though isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes. Mm. A bonus then, but that's going back - twenty years you see that was - days of - no, there's nothing - ever mentioned about - we'
d get - Christmas present at the - year end you see and things like that you see, but that was all. Prior to the war you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Prior to the - up to the end of 1919 were there any welfare schemes of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Only thought - you thought was the work house, that's all - you - I - I - sorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 I meant within the firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, it started after the war I think bits of - there was a sickness - started - you know, so much I think sixpence a week or something. Well they took sixpence I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Would you say that starting full time work changed your attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
No, I took it in me stride, I didn't think a lot about - you see - I always look at this, what has to be will be and - it seems to go on all - all my life you see, I haven'
t sort of rebelled against any - anything much you see, I - you know, just - accepted it. Because it makes life easier doesn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You continued to live at home when you started work didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, I - you see that, the stepmother, the first o
ne you see - ten year old to twenty four when I got married, see fourteen years, well it was very happy during that time, she was very good to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did starting work change your relationship with your father and her at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, I don't think so, 
you see. I might have rebelled about - having to drop some spending money from a shilling to ninepence like and - you know, she - she - and I was growing older you see but it still got back to a shilling in due course afterwards. Of course that's naturall
y isn't it after all, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did starting work full time alter your relationship with your brothers and sisters at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, perhaps felt a bit independent you see like you - you would, growing up and you - yes. I was one of them like that.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you spend your Sunday any differently, or did you still go on going to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes, oh yes, mm. I dodged off sometimes like you know. Oh yes. That's right, yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, never, until - they talked too muc
h in the war and after the war you see and - the crowd I was with - all Labour you see, I - I did once vote Labour and funny we got - just after the war when - first world war you see and - I voted - For Lee Smith the local - he wasn't a local man, Postma
s
ter General he got - I voted Labour then and then it - when I got into business and all that and - I sort of changed because - although I'd voted Labour me father was a Conservative you see. Well all - all seem to do it, and the war comes and the - they a
ll - they sort of swing to Labour you see troops you know, having a change you know. Gradually go back you see I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you vote in an election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. No. No, you see I - I'd just be twenty-one you see. I'd be away and I don't think
 - we - when I came home you see I'd vote, I wouldn't vote whilst I was away. I was twenty-one when I served at Blackpool just towards the end of the war but - never voted 'til I came out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Before you actually went away in the war did you have any political views at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Had any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you have any political views at all before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Not really just affected - we were Conservatives and that was it you see. I think that seemed to be - but, it was - usually - Keighley was - always Liberal y
ou see, so - and they always said - Sir John Brigg - well he said if they put a - donkey up in Keighley and put a yellow ribbon on they'll vote for it, Liberal you see in those days, that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you take part in political activities before you went away to the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, but I did - between the wars you see, or soon after the war, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But before the war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No I didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 You've already told me quite a bit about how you spent your spare time as you were growing up, in the transition from school to work?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When you started work did you continue to carry on with those sort of activities or did you take up new interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, I don't think so, it was more - when you'd done your work you - you mixed with the crowd
 of lads, there was about - six to eight of us were always - gassing and going just - going with the girls in a slight way you know, running about and - and sport you see, we'd go in for sport, we were always - playing cricket when we got a chance and - t
h
ere weren't the things available to us then, cricket grounds and football grounds like there are now, and running places, we'd - just go where we could on commons or anywhere you see. But we carried on with them just the same and - we - we'd get as much p
leasure out of them and we - seen getting money together to start a football team and all that you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
If you were attending evening classes three evenings a week you wouldn't have much opportunity for social activities in the evenings would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you go out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Not much you see - well it - going to evening classes - you - you got friends there you see and you'd gas with them on the way home or stop talking to them and then you'd be home, finished up with y
our supper and to bed. Then the - two evenings, well - sometimes you'd do homework in both of them and sometimes you wouldn't, you'd dodge it, you'd say go out with the boys or something like that. They'd be like - top of the street and - perhaps gassing 
a
nd - perhaps we went to billiard hall or - luckily I never got to the billiard hall, I couldn't afford it. They was earning more money than me so - but - I used to go in with them like, sit and watch them, but I - I couldn't afford to play you see. Billia
rd halls, they were billiard halls. And that was in - in the winter months you see, like in the summer months we were always out somewhere. Cricket, football or running.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you make any new friends about that time when you started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Same 
friends. I got very friendly with a - the one - higher up than me in the office he was a - a - a footballer, he was very good and - we - we didn't go about together but we were - I used to go watch him you see when I was younger 'cos he was - four and a h
alf years I mean the - higher class than me, he was a footballer and I'd go with him to - for his matches sometimes you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did you take your friends home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Oh yes, occasionally you see. Not too much you see but just occasionally. They'd 
come in for me you see, and where - if I wasn't ready - as - for asking them to tea like we didn't do much of that you see. Perhaps a birthday or a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Apart from this boy in the office did you have any other special friends at that time, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What - what age are we at now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 When you'd just started work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No. No. No, I made two at the - evening classes like, two boys there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Two new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 But not sort of on a permanent - basis. I'd maybe go to the pictures Saturday e
vening with them occasionally, and leave this gang you see, I don't know what they were doing but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your parents meet them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 No, knew of them you see. Just occasionally. On the way to they might just pop in for me see and just come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did your parents expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Not at - not really when I was - in like - as long as I was all right they didn't bother you see. Well - didn't like you to be out late at all you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 Did they specify a time for you to be in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Usually like because they went to bed early me father working you see and I had to be up pretty - he had to be up six you see, I hadn't you see, I - I started half past eight, he'd be off early in the morning you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6835765 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 What time did you have to be in at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7481375 SW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10899911\charrsid7673570 
Ten or half past you see in them days. 'Course - evening classes the later one's at half past nine, well I could never - be in much before ten you see. But the first early one - was - was 'til nine o'clock you see,
 I could be home sooner. But as I say - having been there - the - the boys - friends were about, see them gassing you see, well I - I might join them you see naturally stop a bit longer talking to them before I went home. But there was no time for much - 
a
nything else during that period Which was the winter period naturally. Because there were no - evening classes in the summer in those days, it was winter months and - you had more time on your hands, well - make use of it in the light nights you see, you'
d be on the street - on the fields and - commons then.
\par }}